title: bread pudding
directions: Grease large casserole with butter.
Soak bread in milk; mix well with hands.
Beat eggs with sugar, flavorings, raisins and cinnamon (nuts if desired).
Mix well with bread.
Cook, uncovered, in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap bacon strip around each piece of chicken.
Spread dried beef on bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken and mushroom caps on top of beef. Combine sour cream, soup and sherry and spread on top of chicken.
Bake in 300 degree oven for 2 hours uncovered.
If casserole is too brown after cooking 1 hour, place a piece of foil lightly over top and finish cooking.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef roulades or roll
directions: Allow one roulades or roll per person. Have the butcher cut strips of aged hind shank. Ask him to take care that the strips are not cut too thinly. At home dry the pieces of meat with paper towels. Spread on side of the meat with salt and pepper. Turn the meat and spread the meat with mustard. Place a strip of smoked bacon in the center of each strip and top with one small sliced onion and a slice of pickle. Fold over sides and roll beginning with the narrow end of the beef shank. Fasten or tie with cotton thread, toothpicks or roulades needles.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients but chicken.
Pour in large casserole dish.
Place chicken on top.
Bake at 250°, uncovered, for 3 hours.

title: smoked sausage noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to box directions.
Melt butter in small pan over medium heat.
Saute onion and celery until crisp-tender.
Combine noodles, onion, celery, corn, sour cream, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Pour into buttered, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Cut sausage into serving size pieces.
Arrange on top of noodles and push down partially into noodles.
Bake 40 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: polenta with meat sauce
directions: In glass measure, combine broth and corn meal.
Blend until very thick, stirring occasionally.
Add butter or margarine, Mozzarella cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir.

title: swiss and turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the nuts.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole and sprinkle on the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 6.
Adding 1/4 cup wine enhances the beauty of this simple, delicious dish.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and spread thin down the center of the shells.
Roll and seal by using finger and adding a little water on 1/4-inch of shell; press together.
Freeze and then cut into 1/2-inch slices with a serrated knife.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Cover and bake in slow oven (275°) for 6 hours.

title: pork chops and orange sauce
directions: Brown pork chops.
Simmer in orange juice and water for 30 to 40 minutes, until done.
Thicken with cornstarch and water mixture.
Top with paprika.

title: angel dream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Measure sifted flour.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift together 4 times.
Combine egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and flavorings in a large bowl.
Beat with sturdy beater until moist peaks form.
Add 1 1/3 cups of sugar in additions, folding in with large wire spoon.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Run spoon around edge 2 times to get rid of bubbles. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Cool cake upside down in pan, resting on cake rack.
Yields 16 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in uncooked pie crust.
Cover with crust.
Sprinkle top of pie with sugar, cinnamon, butter and Pet milk.
Bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring to a boil and turn over beets that have been cooked and skins taken off and packed in jars.

title: southern perfect eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Beat egg whites.
Add remaining sugar gradually, until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into beaten yolks.
Stir cream and milk into egg mixture.
Add brandy and rum.
Stir thoroughly. Sprinkle nutmeg over each serving.
Chill.
Yields 5 pints.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and bacon and toss lightly to coat.
Marinate 1 hour at least.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugars.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour and baking powder.
Fold in nuts.
Form into rolls 6 to 12 inches long.
Wrap in wax paper; chill.
When chilled firm, slice thin. Bake on cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: baked pasta family style
directions: In a large pan brown beef and garlic in oil.
Saute meat until tender and drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients, except cheese (for top) and pasta.
Simmer the mixture while pasta cooks until barely tender.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in a pan.
Dip marshmallows in mixture and roll in Rice Krispies.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Drop in pecans.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Quarter biscuits and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Drop in Bundt pan.
Over low heat, melt butter and stir in brown sugar until it dissolves.
Pour over top of biscuit quarters.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine wet ingredients.
In a separate bowl combine dry ingredients.
Stir wet mixture into dry mixture.
Allow to stand for 30 minutes, or until oats have absorbed some of the liquid. Preheat oven to 325°.
Drop mixture by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven for 12 minutes.
Yields 50 cookies.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
Beat egg yolks; add 3/4 cup of the corn syrup (or 1/2 of the sugar), lemon juice and salt.
Cook in double boiler until custard consistency, stirring constantly. Add softened gelatine and stir until dissolved.
Add grated rind. Cool and when the mixture begins to thicken, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites to which remaining corn syrup or sugar has been added.
Turn into baked pie shell or crumb crust and chill. Sprinkle with chopped walnuts, if desired.

title: apple walnut supreme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine apples and sugar.
Set aside.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato, cool and mash. Place in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar a litte at a time, mixing with electric mixer.
Keep adding sugar until it can be rolled into a ball like dough.
Sprinkle more sugar on table top. Cut dough in half. Roll out with rolling pin (flat like a pizza).

Keep sugar on rolling pin, to prevent sticking. Spread peanut butter all around dough. Then roll up dough from one end to the other, until rolled into a large tube. Use knife and cut into small slices. Place slices on waxed paper, sprinkle with sugar. Place in refrigerator, until peanut butter hardens.

title: peroshki(makes 60 to 70)
directions: In a 6-quart mixing bowl, mix together mashed potatoes, margarine, 1/2 cup water, eggs, buttermilk, sugar, salt and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Set aside.
Ina small bowl, dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Let rise for 3 to 5 minutes, and then add it to the first mixture, mixing it together well with a wire whip.
Let the dough rise in a warm place.
(To speed up the process, I preheat the oven to 200° and then turn it off.
Set the dough in the warmed oven to rise for about 20 minutes.)
When the dough looks bubbly all over, mix in the remaining flour--going easy with the last 2 cups of flour.
The consistency of the dough should be very soft and not too stiff.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine self-rising corn meal, sugar and onion in bowl.
Add milk and egg to dry ingredients, stirring to combine.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into hot deep fat (375°), frying only a few at a time.
Fry until golden brown; drain on absorbent paper.

title: shrimp butter spread
directions: Let cream cheese and margarine soften.
Mix together all of the ingredients with a fork.
Refrigerate.
Serve on crackers.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat eggs for 3 minutes.
Add sugar and cream until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla, salt and condensed milk and mix well. Next add evaporated milk and crushed Butterfingers.
Mix well. Pour into ice cream container.
Fill with whole milk until container fill line.
Freeze until hard.

title: salad spread or dip
directions: Mix together and chill in refrigerator at least 2 hours. Serve.

title: coating mix for chicken or pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Coat pieces of meat.
Lay pieces of coated meat in open flat pan.
Butter or margarine can be drizzled over all pieces or bake plain to reduce fat.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours depending on thickness of meat.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Melt margarine in scalded milk.
Refrigerate and let cool. Combine water, 3 tablespoons sugar and yeast.
Combine with cooled milk.
Add 5 to 6 cups flour, sugar, eggs and salt.
Keep sticky and let rise for about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again until double.

title: milky way bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup evaporated milk, butter/margarine and eggs in mixing bowl until well blended. Spread half of this batter in a greased/floured 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Melt caramel candies with 1/3 cup evaporated milk (the easiest way to do this is in your microwave in a glass microwave safe bowl).
Spread candy mixture over cake batter.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over candy mixture.
Top with remaining cake batter and return to oven.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: little nibblers
directions: Beat egg white with sweetener, cinnamon, coffee and nutmeg until egg white is foamy (a little stiff).
Add Shredded Wheat and nuts.
Toss lightly to coat with egg white mixture.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until cereal is crisp.
Stir occasionally to separate pieces.
Cool.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter until wilted.
Blend flour in well.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, salt, red pepper and black pepper; cook 5 minutes.
Place crabmeat in a casserole dish and mix in cooked sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in bacon grease, and combine with lima beans and bacon.
Add tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Put into greased casserole.
Top with cheese slices and heat until bubbly, uncovered, at 350 degrees.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift together flour and sugar into bowl.
Add egg, sour cream, vanilla and nutmeg.
Beat to smooth thin batter.
Blend in apples and pour
into
pie
shell.
Bake
at
for
15 minutes, then 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: lemon parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in margarine and lemon juice, then bread crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Bake uncovered at 350° about an hour.

title: seminole indian pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together and form small ball shapes, flatten and fry in oil.
May use white sugar after cooking, if you like.

title: pepperidge farm hors d'oeuvre
directions: Saute sausage and ground beef; drain grease from meat.
Mix all ingredients together in a large skillet until cheese melts. Spread top of each slice of bread with meat mixture.
Flash freeze (about 15 minutes) and then put in Ziploc bag and place in freezer.
When you are ready to serve, take the number you wish to serve from bag, place on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° to 400° oven until hot.
Serve immediately.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Make a layer of each ingredient in a large salad bowl.
Cover salad with dressing and cheese and serve.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: johnny sandusky
directions: Brown beef, celery and onion. Drain.
Mix macaroni, tomatoes and green pepper.
Let set overnight.
Sprinkle grated cheese liberally on top and bake slowly at 325° for 60 minutes.
May add garlic.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes; cool.
Bake cake according to directions on package.
While cake is hot, poke holes in top.
Pour cooled pineapple mixture on top of cake; spread. Whip together pudding, cream cheese and milk.
Cover cake with this mixture.
Let set in refrigerator 1 or 2 days.

title: easy potatoes and mushrooms
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Drain mushrooms well.
Mix potatoes, mushrooms and dry soup mix good.
Put in casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Pour oil over this evenly. Cover with aluminum foil; bake at about 325° to 350° until potatoes are tender.
Uncover; bake about 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Put wafers in muffin papers.
Beat until creamy remaining ingredients.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Top with favorite fruit (strawberries, raspberries, blueberries, cherries).
Cool in refrigerator.

title: shrimp and scallop pilaf(serves 4)
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and stir in turmeric over medium heat.
Add rice, onion and garlic.
Cook about 3 minutes, until onion is translucent and stirring often.
Pour in broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, scallops and peas.
Simmer, covered, 5 to 10 minutes, until scallops are opaque and shrimp is pink and peas are warm.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in shortening. Pour off drippings.
Combine soup, milk and water.
Pour over chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Stir gravy and serve over rice.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease (spray) a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Tear up bread (remove crust, if desired) in bowl (size is not important). Sprinkle with cinnamon and drizzle melted margarine.
Add raisins and coconut.
Combine eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and rum.
Pour over bread.
Lightly stir until all ingredients are well mixed. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Melt margarine and pour into egg.
Add sugar, pineapple and coconut.
Mix well and pour into pie crust. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: creamy cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple.
Stir together sour cream and powdered sugar.
Add to fruit mixture.
Line a 3-cup refrigerator tray with foil.
Pour in fruit mixture.
Freeze firm.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Combine; mix well all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes (or until done) at 350°.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream butter with white sugar and eggs.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt, coffee and vanilla.
Fold in chopped apples.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Sprinkle over batter in pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream (optional).

title: pink party salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Don't add any cold water to it.
Add pineapple juice.
Cool until almost set.
Blend in banana, apple, nuts and whipping cream.
Place in a large bowl until set.
Serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Use portion of butter to grease 2-quart casserole.
Add corn. Sprinkle with flour and salt; stir well.
In separate bowl, lightly beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Add remainder of butter and stir well.
Bake at 325°.
Stir once during cooking.

title: milky wonder cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1/2 cup butter in saucepan over low heat. Beat remaining 1/2 cup butter and sugar in medium size bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with buttermilk.
Stir until smooth.
Add melted candy, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour in tube pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Frost (recipe follows).

title: hawaiian sweet potatoes
directions: Mix and spread in a glass dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine 1 cup of flour with yeast, salt and sugar.
Add warm water, butter and egg.
Stir together.
Add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time.
Blend well until dough is not sticky.
Knead on floured surface until smooth.
Put into greased bowl and cover well; refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, shape rolls and place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 16 rolls.
Brush with butter.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs.
Mix well the beaten eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar.
Add the zucchini.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together and stuff peppers.
Put in large kettle.
Cover with tomato juice.
Cook on low heat 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until done.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: penuche candy
directions: Combine sugar, salt and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture bonds. Continue cooking until soft ball stage (236°).
Stir frequently after mixture begins to thicken. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool without stirring until lukewarm.
Add nuts.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: baked beans
directions: Cover beans in boiling water.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. Drain beans; reserve the liquid.

title: broccoli barley soup
directions: In 5 quart sauce pan, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook until soft.
Add rosemary, vegetable stock, and barley.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until barley is tender, about 45 minutes.
Remove broccoli flowerets and cut into bit size pieces.
Peel stems and slice thinly.
When barley is tender increase heat, adding broccoli. Cover; cook until tender and still bright green, about 10 minutes. Stir together cornstarch and water.
Add to soup along with milk. Stir until soup boils and thickens.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle each serving lightly with cheese.

title: chunky salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours. Serve with chips or meat.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter in pie dish. Combine other ingredients and mix until smooth. Add melted butter and stir well. Pour mixture back in pie dish. Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except broccoli.
Put the broccoli in a baking dish.
Pour mixture on top of broccoli and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: almond bark
directions: Combine pretzels, pecans and Rice Krispies in a bowl.
Melt chocolate slowly; do not introduce any water.
Pour chocolate over mixture and stir to coat.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir gently.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: spice surprise cake
directions: Sift
flour
if you wish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two layer pans

Cream butter and sugar.

Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture.

Beat egg whites until stiff, but

into creamed mixture. Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake

layers and oblong 37 to 40 minutes.
Bake 9-inch layers about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with desired frosting.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Use as a dip for all fruits.

title: gloria's quick and easy bean dip
directions: Mash beans and fry until dry.
Top with grated cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: melancholy bars
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend
all ingredients together.
Chill, and serve with your choice of mixed fresh vegetables.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Deep fry or bake chicken wings.
In a mixing bowl combine melted butter, hot sauce and Heinz 57 sauce.
Mix well.
Add paprika and cayenne pepper (be careful with the cayenne pepper; add to taste, the more pepper the hotter the wings).
Note:
The mixture will not taste as it will on the wings.
Put wings into baking pan.
Add sauce, stir gently then bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with celery and Blue cheese dressing.

title: caramel cake icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar and bring to a boil. Add milk and bring to a boil again. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and enough powdered sugar to make desired consistency. Beat several minutes and frost cool cake.
Makes enough icing for 2 cakes.
May keep in refrigerator.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into containers.
Freeze to a slush.
Add 7-Up when ready to serve.

title: german sour cream twists
directions: Sift flour and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir into flour mixture with sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well, using hands, if necessary.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: own crust coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pie pan. Will make 1-3 pies depending on size of pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Middle will appear soft, but the pie will have a delicate crust on the top, sides and bottom.

title: hot mexican cornbread
directions: Mix
together cornmeal, buttermilk, corn, peppers, eggs and Cheddar
cheese.
Melt margarine and add to mixture; pour into a 9
x 12-inch pan (a nonstick pan works best).
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: soprasta (salami) pesto bread
directions: Roll (stretch) each dough (loaf on jelly sheet).
Skim oil from pesto sauce and discard.
Spread pesto sauce, leave an edge without pesto sauce, not too much.
Then add salami slices.
Then add sliced Mozzarella on top.
You can also add thin sliced onion rings and tomatoes if you like.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Spread bananas over filling and then pineapple over bananas. Spread whipped topping over pineapple and top with nuts (optional).

title: frito-lay chicken casserole
directions: Cut or tear chicken into bite-size pieces; set aside.
Mix soup, water and milk until creamy; set aside.

In a casserole dish, layer the ingredients, beginning with the Frito Lay corn chips, then chicken, soup (just enough to hold casserole together), and finally sprinkle cheese. Repeat until pan will hold no more. Try to end up with cheese on the top; it melts nicely. It is okay to have almost half of your soup mixture remaining when done; discard what you do not use. Bake casserole at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes. Serve hot. Can garnish with salsa and/or sour cream.

title: bacon wands(microwave)
directions: Wrap each bread stick with a bacon slice in a spiral.
Place 6 at a time on paper towel lined plate.
Cover with paper towel. Microwave 6 minutes on High or until bacon is crisp, turning once.

title: make ahead lettuce salad
directions: Shred lettuce on platter.
Dice 4 stalks celery.
Slice one small onion.
Put on top the sour cream mixed well with sugar. Drizzle over top the mayonnaise and vinegar (mixed together).
Add crisp fried, drained and broken up bacon.
Crumble and spread over top.
Cover with grated Parmesan cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for several hours.
Serve as is.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion.
Add soup, taco sauce and chiles.
Mix well.
Add Velveeta by slices or small cubes.
Stir until melted and simmering.
Serve from crock-pot with nacho chips.

title: pineapple lime jell-o
directions: Put pineapple with juice in saucepan.
Add water.
Cook until very hot, almost to boiling.
Add jello, stir until dissolved. Set aside to cool.
Cut up cream cheese and stir into jello.
Add cool whip.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat on medium speed until blended.
Good on fruit or pound cake cubes.

title: dieter's delite cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup brown sugar over margarine.

title: spicy beef with mint
directions: Brown ground beef or pork, without oil, until the pink is gone.
Place in a mixing bowl; let cool for 5 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, warm water and vanilla.
Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add mayonnaise mixture to dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into square or rectangular cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer spinach with lettuce; add salt and pepper, almonds, raw zucchini, frozen peas, bacon, scallions/onions, shredded cheese and boiled eggs.
Pour 2 cups Ranch dressing over.
Let set for 6 hours.
Garnish with bread crumbs, shredded cheese and sliced almonds.

title: cherry oat dessert squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl mix sugar, nuts, oats, butter and flour until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remainder into bottom of 9-inch square baking dish.
Stir cinnamon into cherry filling.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top, pressing lightly.
Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Prep time:
10 minutes.
Makes 16 squares.

title: mammaw's onion rings
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings (about 3/8-inch thick). Soak rings in a bowl of milk for 1 hour (use enough milk to cover rings).
Remove the rings from the milk and set aside in another bowl.
To milk, add enough flour until you have a thick batter (thick enough to really stick to rings).
Dip each ring into the batter until well coated.
Fry in deep fryer (oil hot) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix and cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 3 tablespoons strawberry jello.
Let stand to room temperature.
Add strawberries.
Put in a cooked deep dish pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: shrimp etouffee(cajun)
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Then add shrimp and seasonings and red pepper to taste.
Over low heat, cover and let steam about 15 to 20 minutes, until shrimp are done.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: bean and frito salad(mexico)
directions: Drain beans; combine with onion.
Marinate in French dressing for a few hours or overnight.
Add lettuce broken into bite size pieces, grated cheese and corn chips broken into small pieces. Toss and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Use half of the pecans in mixture and roll in other half.

title: crockpot corn
directions: Place all ingredients in crockpot. Cook on low about 6 hours. Very rich and creamy.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: In top of buttered boiler, melt morsels over boiling water. Stir in sweetened condensed milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and peanuts.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place buttered bread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then put cheese on top of bread.
Next take fried sausage and crumble on top of cheese.
Mix milk with beaten eggs and pour on top.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange in blender.
Add in sugar and blend.
Pour into bowl and let mixture set for 30 minutes.

title: beef tips on rice
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in plastic bag; shake to mix. Place beef cubes in bag and shake.	Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add beef and cook until brown.	Add onion and cook until tender.
Add beef broth; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: green chili
directions: Cut meat into small cubes and cook until partly tender in water.
Drain broth of meat and save.
In large skillet with 1 tablespoon oil, brown meat.
Add onion and flour.
Add broth of meat, garlic, green chili, salt and cumin.
Simmer for 1 hour. Delicious when served with refried beans and white flour tortillas.
Top with lettuce, tomato, onion and cheese.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine tomato sauce, sugar and mustard.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and one-half of the sauce mixture.
Put into ring-shaped microwave pan (looks like Bundt pan).
Press in mixture and top with remaining sauce.
Cook, uncovered, on High 14 to 16 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix together in a bowl with a fork the flour, shortening, salt and sugar.
Stir together and add to flour mixture the egg, vinegar and water.
Chill for 15 minutes or more.
Then roll out for pie crusts or shape into balls.
Flatten and freeze.
Thaw and roll out into the flakiest pie crusts ever.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water. Stir in Eagle Brand and egg yolks. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Cool slightly. Slice 2 bananas, dip in lemon juice and drain. Arrange on bottom of pie shell.
Pour filling over bananas and cover. Chill 4 hours until set.
Spread top with whipped cream. Slice remaining banana, dip in lemon juice, drain and garnish top of pie.

title: pat nicholson's ham rolls
directions: Turn out entire
pan
of
rolls
intact,
upside
down. Slice through rolls and
return
the
bottom
half to the roll pan. Layer ham and
cheese
slices on bottom portion of rolls and cover with top
portion
of rolls.
Mix all other ingredients and pour evenly
over
rolls.
Let
sit
until mixture is absorbed (15 to 20
minutes).
Cover
with aluminum foil.
At this stage, rolls can be heated, refrigerated or frozen.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes
or until cheese melts.
Slice through at normal roll separations
(bake
covered).
When
frozen, I move to refrigerator the
night
before so heating is about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 48 rolls.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate potatoes into milk.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in 12 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan at 400° for 1 hour, until firm and lightly brown.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Season chicken with Garlic Season-All.
Put in the refrigerator for approximately 20 minutes.
In the meantime, cut up all vegetables to the size you would make them for a dip.
In a large skillet, heat oil and butter on medium-high heat until foamy.
Add chicken and cook until white on both sides.
Add all the vegetables and stir.
Keep a lid on the skillet in between stirring.
Cook until vegetables are done.

title: honey banana bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add wheat germ also, if desired.
In separate bowl, beat together oil, honey, egg, bananas and vanilla.
Beat flour into banana mixture until moist.
Add pecans.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: yogurt shakes
directions: Whirl orange juice concentrate, yogurt and milk in blender container until smooth.
Pour into 2 tall glasses. Top each with a large scoop of orange sherbet.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired.

title: barbecued pork sandwiches(this recipe uses less sugar and salt than other recipes.)
directions: Trim fat off roast and cut into 1-inch cubes.
In a small roasting pan, combine all ingredients and bake, covered, until meat falls apart.
Skim off all fat.
Remove and shred meat. Return to cooking sauce, mix well, heat and serve.
One large serving equals 9 grams fat.
Can be frozen and warmed in preheated oven.

title: dr. pepper cake
directions: Heat butter, cocoa, and Dr. Pepper. Set aside. Mix eggs, sugar, buttermilk, baking soda, vanilla, and cinnamon. Add Dr. Pepper and buttermilk mixtures to flour and mix well.
Place in will greased and floured round cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Cool and frost with Dr. Pepper Icing.

title: fruit bar
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in medium bowl.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat together margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add combined flour, oats and the 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Beat until crumbly.
Reserve 3/4 cup oats mixture for topping.
Press remaining oat mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Spread fruit evenly over crust to within 1/4-inch of edge.
Combine nuts and reserved oats mixture, sprinkle over fruit evenly.
Pat down lightly.
Bake 16 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 32 bars.

title: crunchy beef casserole
directions: Cook
macaroni
and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain off excess
fat.
Combine
all ingredients, except the French fried onions.
Put in a greased 4 quart casserole.
Cover and bake
for 30
minutes
Uncover, top with the French fried onions and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: bacon-swiss tossed salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, salt and pepper. In large salad bowl, layer a third of the greens and a third of the mayonnaise mixture, onion, peas and cheese.
Repeat the layers twice.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, add the bacon and toss.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna strips until done.
Drain and dry off.
Mix together the egg, parsley flakes, Ricotta cheese, nutmeg, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar with 1/2 cup cold water; bring to a boil. Dissolve cornstarch in 3/4 cup cold water; add salt, coloring and lemon juice.
Gradually add to water sugar, stirring constantly until thick.
Place strawberries in baked pie crust.
Pour in mixture; top with whip topping.

title: microwave cheesy potato casserole
directions: Pierce hash brown potato package.
Cook the potatoes 3 to 4 minutes, rotating one quarter turn halfway through cooking time.

title: deer jerky
directions: Marinate strips of deer meat in mixture overnight.
Then put directly on racks of oven at 150° for 6-8 hours.
The longer it is baked, the crispier it will be.
Put in air-tight bags or containers.
They say it will keep for 2 years, but I think you'd have to hide it!

title: marinated crab
directions: Mix all ingredients except crab. Marinate for 8 or more hours.

title: green chili
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add chopped onion and minced garlic.
Cook until onion and garlic are soft.
Add beans, chilies and Ro-Tel.
Add beef stock or bouillon to cover; sprinkle on comino and simmer until potatoes are done.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 25 to 30 minutes or until tender. Drain and cool 10 to 15 minutes; cut into 1/4-inch thick slices and set aside.

title: fresh salmon phyllo puff(two to 3 puffs will serve 1 person.)
directions: Thaw box of phyllo dough.
Carefully section one sheet of paper thin phyllo dough into 3 pieces.
Work with only 1 sheet at a time keeping others covered in the box.
(After box of phyllo is thawed, unused portion can be refrozen.) Spray phyllo sheets with cooking spray until moist.
Layer the 3 sheets together, one on top of the other.
(An alternative is to fold a single phyllo sheet into thirds.) You will end up with a phyllo section approximately 3-inches wide and 14-inches long.
Sprinkle the top sheet with 1/4 teaspoon curry.
Place a 2 ounce piece of salmon fillet on the corner at one end of the top sheet.
Top salmon with 1 teaspoon lemon juice, 2 thin slices of ginger, 1 or 2 slices of mushroom, 2 thin slices of zucchini and a pinch of salt.
Fold pastry with stuffing into a triangle and keep folding back and forth down the 14-inch length.
Prepare 2 to 3 puffs per person. Bake on a pan, covered with cooking spray, in a 400° oven for 25 minutes until crispy and golden brown.

title: heavenly cheesecake
directions: *If liqueur is used, use 4 eggs.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Grease muffin tins; fill 3/4 full.
After mixing set in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.
Fill pans then bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Drain carrots; add salt, onions and peppers.
Cook mixture of soup, sugar, vinegar and oil for 3 minutes at least.
Pour this mixture over vegetables.
Mix well.
Cover and chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: orange cookies
directions: Blend sugar and shortening.
Add egg; mix in orange juice and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Stir orange peel in batter, if desired.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: marinated shish kabobs
directions: Trim
fat
off
meat.	Combine
remaining
ingredients except mushrooms, peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Marinate meat in this mixture for 6 hours, turning often.
Add mushrooms and pepper wedges to
marinating
sauce.
Marinate
2	more hours. When ready to	assemble,
alternate
meat, peppers, onions and tomatoes (wedges or	whole,	small
tomatoes)
on
skewers and broil about 20	minutes,
basting often with marinating sauce. (May be cooked on the outdoor grill.) Yields 4 servings.

title: 6-cup salad
directions: Combine coconut, marshmallows, pineapple, oranges and blueberries in a bowl; mix well.
Fold in yogurt.
Yields 8 servings.
Per serving:
127 calories, 4 g fat, 0.5 mg chol, 56 mg Na.

title: taco salad
directions: In large salad bowl or individual salad bowls, place ingredients in order.
Pour creamy Italian dressing over salad and serve.
If prepared early, add chips and dressing just before serving to keep chips crisp.
Sliced red onion rings over top of salad makes this very attractive.

title: farm-style chili con queso
directions: Cook bacon until most of the fat is removed.
Add onion, tomato and celery.
Cook over medium heat until onion is tender. Stir in salsa and salt.
Add cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
Do not let boil.
Keep warm for dipping.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: thanksgiving chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until done (do not salt).
Remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth.
Melt margarine and stir in dressing and onions (celery and sage).
In a greased 9 x 13 casserole dish, begin with a layer of dressing crumbs.
Add a layer of chicken, then a layer of mushroom soup, diluted with 1 can of reserved chicken broth.
Again, a layer of crumbs and chicken, then a can of cream of chicken soup diluted with 1 can of reserved chicken broth.
Top with crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until top is brown.
Serves 10 - 12.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a loaf.
Place in a nonstick loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may double recipe, if so, double everything, including cooking time.

title: raspberry topping
directions: Drain 2/3 cup syrup from raspberries.
Combine syrup and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened and clear.
Cool.
Stir in raspberries.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: black bean soup
directions: Cook bacon over medium-high heat in large saucepan until crisp.
Remove to paper towels; set aside.
Add onion and garlic to drippings; cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add beans and liquid, broth, water, 3/4 cup picante sauce, salt and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Ladle into soup bowls; dollop with sour cream. Sprinkle with reserved bacon.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix to the sour cream the soup, milk, salt, onion, half of the margarine and add thawed potatoes.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and arrange cheese over top.
Add crushed corn flakes on top of cheese and dribble rest of margarine over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mission gazpacho(makes 12 servings)
directions: Peel and dice tomatoes without losing any juice.
Peel and dice the cucumbers, onion and green pepper.
Rub a large bowl with garlic clove and add all ingredients.
Stir and chill.

title: broiled lake trout
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place trout in shallow dish.
Combine salt and water; pour over fish.
Let stand 8 to 10 minutes; drain. Combine oil and pepper; brush fish with mixture.
Place trout on broiler pan, skin side up, about 2-inches from heat source.
Broil for 5 minutes.
Baste with more peppered oil.
Turn over and broil until well browned.
Transfer trout to heated platter.
Brush with melted butter.
Serve garnished with lemon slices.

title: macaroni apple salad
directions: Combine macaroni, apples, celery, mayonnaise and yogurt in medium bowl.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine giblets in water in saucepan.
Cook until giblets are no longer pink.
Reserve two cups broth (set aside giblets), chop and add to gravy.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Saute celery and onion until transparent.
Add bread crumbs and cornbread seasonings.
Pour reserved broth over ingredients and stir to blend.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook, covered with aluminum foil, for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes, or can be stuffed in cavity of chicken or turkey and roast as desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place peeled and sliced potatoes, raw, in a 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Cut
onions
in
relatively small pieces and place atop
potatoes.
Add mushrooms.
Spread evenly.
Spread broken up raw hamburger over this.
Spread undiluted soup evenly over all. All
ingredients
are
placed
into
casserole dish raw. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more, depending on your oven, until tender.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat the peanut butter, sugars, butter, eggs and soda together well.
Beat in the flour.
Place on cookie sheet in little balls about the size of the end of your finger.
Place 2 inches apart and mash down with fork.
Bake at 350° until light tan, about 6 to 8 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and juices from fruit cocktail.
Mix.
Then add fruit cocktail.
Stir until well blended.
Grease and flour an oblong baking dish (9 x 2 x 12-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Get wax paper; flour it.
Roll dough with rolling pin real thin.
Cut with cookie cutter and place on lightly greased pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375° or until done.

title: s'mores(microwave)
directions: Place chocolate onto graham cracker.
Place marshmallow on top of chocolate.
Top with the other graham cracker.
Place on napkin and cook in microwave as follows:
For 1 S'more, 15 seconds, for 2 S'mores, 25 seconds and for 3 S'mores, 35 seconds, and so on.

title: stroganoff meatballs
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, milk, onion, green peppers and seasoned salt in a mixing bowl.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape the mixture into an 8 x 6-inch rectangle.
Divide into 48 pieces. Roll each piece into a meatball.
Place meatballs in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes or until no pink remains.
Drain.
If desired cover and chill for up to 24 hours.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in large skillet. Add next 5 ingredients; toss lightly to mix. Spread in greased baking dish. Arrange chicken over dressing. Melt shortening in saucepan; blend in flour. Stir in broth. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Cool slightly; blend in eggs. Cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over chicken. Top with dried bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown. Yield: 12 servings.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add buttermilk.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt and add to mixture.
Blend in bananas.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in hot oil in skillet.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to simmer. Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Add green pepper slices during last 5 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla.
Add cream cheese and whip until stiffened.
Spread onto graham cracker crust.
Spoon cherry pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Chill for 24 hours before serving.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix the ingredients except hot dogs together.
Dip the hot dogs in the batter and deep fry (use solid Crisco) until golden brown on medium heat.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, sugar and 1/3 teaspoon salt.
Beat well and add chocolate chips.
Set aside.

title: sweet fruit muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups or use paper liners.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Add dry ingredients and fruit.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
This recipe can easily be doubled or halved.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place ribs in shallow roasting pan, meaty side up.
On each piece, place a slice of unpeeled lemon, a thin slice of onion. Roast in hot oven (450°) for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to boiling and pour over ribs.
Continue baking in moderate oven (350° ) until tender, about 45 minutes to 1 hour. Baste ribs with the sauce every 15 minutes.
If sauce gets too thick, add more water.
Serves 4.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Combine crackers, walnuts and baking powder.
Fold into egg mixture with vanilla.
Spread in a buttered 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until dry.
Cool and spread with sweetened whipped cream.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream pie
directions: Scald 1 3/4 cups milk with Karo in microwave.
Mix cornstarch, remaining 1/4 cup milk, sugar, salt and beaten egg yolks in double boiler.
Add scalded milk to mixture.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1 tablespoon margarine.
May add coconut, bananas or cocoa to make a different pie.
Top with Cool Whip when pie is cool.

title: spinach salad
directions: Add all ingredients in a bowl.

title: gingerbread
directions: Melt shortening and let it cool. Mix with sugar and egg. Mix in molasses. Alternate hot water with flour and spices. Do not over mix. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. If oven cooks hot, cook at 325° for a longer time. Let the bread stand for 15 minutes before removing from the pan. Freezes well.

title: country style linebacker ribs(perfect for tailgating)
directions: Sauce:
Cook onion and garlic in oil for a few minutes.
Add other ingredients and bring to a simmer.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spicy chicken wings
directions: Heat ingredients with oil for 5 minutes.
Pour over wings; bake for 1 hour, or until done.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix butter with sugar, milk and cocoa.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
(Should be at soft ball stage, about 230° on a candy thermometer.)
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Makes about 2 dozen good-size cookies.

title: round or chuck steak casserole
directions: Cut steak into 4 pieces.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and paprika.
Coat with flour.
Brown in hot fat in heavy skillet. Transfer to casserole.
Place onion and potatoes over top.
Mix tomatoes, ketchup and remaining teaspoon salt; pour over potatoes. Cover and bake in 350°
oven for 1 1/4 hours.
If necessary add a little water.

title: ramen beef stroganoff
directions: In a small saucepan cook the beef with one half tbsp. of margarine until no longer pink. Add 1/2 c. water to the pan and the beef seasoning packet. Cook for 3 minutes. Meanwhile, cook the noodles, drain well, and stir in 1 tbsp. of margarine. Add the sour cream to the beef mixture and thicken with flour. Serve sauce over the noodles.

title: original bob evans thousand island
directions: Put all ingredients, except egg and olives, in blender. Process on medium-low speed until vegetables are just coarsely chopped.
Add egg and olives.
Process again until just chopped.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add eggs and milk.
Boil until thick over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell. Cover with meringue (recipe follows).
Bake for approximately 10 minutes at 350° until meringue is golden brown.

title: savory sausage casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage; drain fat.
Add pepper, onion and celery.
Saute until vegetables are slightly tender. Cook grits in water with salt according to package.
Combine cooked grits and sausage mixture.
Pour into buttered shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread undiluted soup over sausage mixture, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy chicken dinner
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes. Cut into slices.
Peel and cut carrots into 1-inch slices.
Chop onion.
Place in crock-pot.
Put frozen chicken pieces on top of vegetables.
Pour soup over top of chicken.
Salt and pepper, if desired. Cook on high for 1 hour, then turn to low.
Serves 4.

title: rich biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Cut in butter and Crisco.
Add milk and stir.
On floured surface, place the dough, forming a ball.
Sprinkle a little flour on top and roll out about 1 1/2 inches thick.
Cut out biscuits and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup together, stirring constantly, until mixture will spin a thread.
Add peanuts and stir constantly until peanuts "pop" in the syrup as it is stirred.
Add butter and soda; mix well.
Spread thin on greased surface.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil sides and bottom of loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into loaf pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Saute onion and bacon in butter until tender and brown.
Set aside.
Mix cheese and flour until covered and set aside.
Mix cream, milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add onion and bacon mix, cheese mix and chicken.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Cover edges of crust with foil.
Done when knife comes clean from middle.

title: pickled yellow squash
directions: Place squash in a large nonaluminum container.
Combine water and pickling salt, stirring until salt dissolves.
Pour over squash.
Cover and let stand 1 hour, drain well.
Combine sugar and next 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Add squash, green pepper and remaining ingredients, bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pack hot vegetables into hot jars, filling to 1/2-inch from top.
Cover with hot vinegar syrup, filling to 1/2-inch from top.
Remove air bubbles.
Wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Yields 4 pints.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In an extra large baking dish, melt 1 stick of butter.
Pour off excess into mixture of potatoes, onions, soup, cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups of bread crumbs over the top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: ev's shortcake(the only real shortcake)
directions: Mix flour,
sugar, baking powder, butter and shortening as for biscuits.
With
a
fork,
beat egg into milk.
Add and mix.
Bake in
greased
round pie or cake pan about 20 minutes in 400° oven. Cool
only
slightly.
With
sharp,
long knife split into two flat
slabs.
Remove
to
large serving plate. Butter bottom
slab generously.
Add
layer
of sugared fruit (strawberries, peaches or boysenberries).
Cover with top slab and add rest of fruit so it spills onto sides of plate.

title: one dish meal
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole.
Peel and slice potatoes into dish. Brown the ground beef.
Put over the potatoes.
Put vegetable soup over meat.
Add other can of soup.
No extra salt needed.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are done.
Cover the casserole.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix sugar, eggs, pumpkin and oil together.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture and mix together.
Add pecans.
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken-fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Spoon individual portions onto salad greens.
Yields 6 servings.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Cut and wash
chicken;
mix
salt,
pepper,
garlic and flour; mix well.
Add
chicken
and
shake
well.
Place
the cooking oil in a frypan and heat hot.
Remove the chicken from flour mixture and into the heated cooking oil.
Fry until done and a golden brown,
20 to 30 minutes;
remove from the frypan and drain on paper towel.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Cream together cream cheese, onion and chives.
Form into small balls.
Roll in grated carrots and serve with toothpicks.

title: macaroni
directions: Aaron said put the macaroni with the cheese.
Cody said next to put the milk in.
Toriah and Dominique said to add the butter. Jennie and Samantha said to put in the ham.
Jonathan said to cook it now.
Troy and Lewis said to mix it up.
All agree to put it in the oven.
Cook for four hours.
(Seth said it would burn.)
He thinks four minutes would be better.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Chop up cabbage and cook until tender, but not mushy; drain. Combine the sugar, vinegar and cornstarch and cook until thick. Add to cabbage.
Fry the bacon until crisp; crumble and add to cabbage.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a small saucepan over low heat until well blended.
Serve warm with apple slices.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread the cream cheese in the bottom of a flat dish.
Spread the taco sauce over the cream cheese.
Top that with sliced olives, green peppers, green onions, mushrooms and then the Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or dip chips.

title: autumn soup
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, melt margarine.
Add vegetables and saute over high heat, stirring frequently until tender.
Add water, squash and broth mixture and combine.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until squash is tender, approximately 15 minutes.
Mash some squash against side of pan.
Add beans and bacon and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serves 2. Contains 279 calories, 7 g fat and 1,056 mg sodium.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt butter with sugar.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into sugar mixture with well beaten eggs.
Fold in vanilla and nuts. Bake in well-greased pan about 30 minutes in
350° oven.

title: roast the vegeburger
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients.
Chill until just set (not hard).
Cream the jello mixture and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: custard pie
directions: Scald milk, sugar and salt.
Stir into beaten eggs, add flavorings.
Pour into unbaked pie shell, sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
To keep the bottom part of the crust from getting soggy, brush with unbeaten egg white.
This is a velvety custard in a tender-crisp pastry.
(I sometimes use 2 cups of milk and 1/2 cup of half and half, instead of 2 1/2 cups of milk.)

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Add cocoa to 1 cup sugar and mix well.
Stir in 2 cups milk slowly to make a smooth mixture.
Heat in double boiler or on low heat in saucepan, stirring constantly.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk in a small saucepan; stir in 1/2 cup sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine water and 2 tablespoons sugar in a large mixing bowl; add yeast, stirring to dissolve. Stir in cooled milk mixture and eggs; mix well.
Add 3 cups flour, mixing well.
Add remaining 3 cups flour and mix well.
Turn dough out on a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic. Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, until doubled in bulk (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch dough down.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 3 in each cup of well-greased muffin pans.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yield:
About 2 1/2 dozen.

title: dieter's dream dessert
directions: Mix well the cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add and stir lightly.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together first six ingredients until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: broccoli deluxe
directions: Cut up broccoli and red onion.
Cook bacon crisp.
Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over the first five.
Stir well.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix sour cream and mayo together until creamy.
Break off flowerets of the cauliflower and put in the mixture.
Chop the green onions and put into the mixture.
Slice the radishes.
Add to the other things.
Mix well.
This gives yu a green and white salad.

title: millionaire pie(2 pies)
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, egg, salt and vanilla.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Chill.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Blend in pineapple and pecans.
Spoon on top of egg mixture and chill thoroughly.

title: butterscotch breakfast rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put dough in pan (still frozen). Sprinkle dry pudding over dough.
Heat butter and brown sugar until melted.
Spoon over dough.
Cover with foil and set in fridge overnight (or let rise and bake).
Uncover.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes to cool, then turn upside-down and serve warm.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Remove 2/3 cup cake mix for filling. Mix remaining cake mix with 1 egg and butter. Pat into a 9 x 13 baking pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool. While cooling, mix syrup, sugar, 3 eggs, vanilla, pecans and 2/3 cup cake mix. Pour over crust and place back in oven for 45 minutes. Cool thoroughly or overnight. Cut into bite-size bars.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together soups and water.
Add rice.
Stir all together well and pour in a well-greased baking dish.
Place pieces of chicken on top and bake for 2 hours at 350°.
For good taste, spread on top Cheez Whiz.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients, mixing dry materials together before adding.
Drop by large spoonfuls onto hot fryer. Reduce heat.
When brown on one side, turn and brown on the other. Serves 6.

title: bakeless cookies
directions: Boil the margarine, sugar and milk; pour over dry ingredients. Mix and drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: adobong baboy (pork adobo)
directions: Place the pork in a medium size pot together with the garlic, soy sauce, pepper and vinegar and let stand for 2 hours.
In the same pot, cook slowly until the pork
is tender (about 30 minutes).
Transfer the pieces of garlic from the pot to a separate pan and fry in hot oil until brown.
Add the pork pieces to the garlic and then fry until brown.
Drain.
Add the broth to the fried pork and garlic and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: onion pie
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions in oil until soft, but not browned; drain well.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley and onions; mix well.
Place in a greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove toys from counter top.
Measure 2 cups flour.
Get baking powder.
Remove kids' hands from flour. Get baking powder.
Remove kids' hands from flour.

title: danish fruit cake
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together; put 1/3 into bowl.
Add the dates, cherries, walnuts and pecans to the 1/3 mixture; mix well and set aside.
Beat the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining 2/3 dry ingredients with buttermilk, orange juice and vanilla (which have been blended well).
Add to fruit and nut mixture; blend well. Turn into a 9-inch greased tube pan, lined with foil and greased again.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: raspberry chicken
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Raise heat; add chicken and cook 3 minutes per side.
Remove from skillet and reserve.
Add onion to fat in pan and cook, covered, over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add vinegar; raise heat and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until reduced to a syrupy spoonful.
Whisk in chicken stock, heavy cream and tomatoes and simmer for 1 minute. Return chicken to skillet and simmer gently, basting often, about 5 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add raspberries to sauce; cook 1 minute.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve immediately.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Wrap wieners in 1/3 strip bacon and attach with toothpick. Place in casserole dish and cover with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until brown sugar is hot and bubbly.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding nuts last.
Chill in refrigerator.
Pinch off small pieces and cook at 325° for 12 minutes.
Makes several dozen.
Dough will keep for days in refrigerator.

title: sourdough rolls
directions: Combine Sourdough Starter, sugar, salt and egg.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Gradually beat in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth, using only enough flour to prevent sticking.
Place in buttered bowl; turn once to bring buttered side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Punch down and shape into balls.
Place balls on greased baking sheets.
Brush with melted butter, cover and let rise.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: cannelloni
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Add onions and garlic, cook over moderate heat.
7 - 8 minutes.
They will be soft, but not brown.
Add dried spinach, stirring constantly and cook 3 - 4 minutes.
When the moisture is cooked away and spinach sticks lightly to the sides of the pan, transfer it to a large mixing bowl.
In the same skillet melt 1 tablespoon butter and lightly brown the ground beef.
Add to spinach mixture.
Add to all the above spinach, meat mixture 5 tablespoon Parmesan cheese, 2 tablespoons heavy cream, the eggs, oregano, salt and pepper.
Mix well and set aside.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, cocoa and eggs together, then add milk, water, flour, baking powder, soda, vanilla and salt.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan (grease and flour first).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease
x
3 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch) loaf pans or 6 (5
x 3 1/4 x 2-inch) loaf pans. Line with greased wax paper.

title: quiche
directions: Mix eggs, cheese and milk in a bowl.
In pie shells, place meat and vegetable, then pour mixture from bowl.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: lemon-pineapple cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg whites (at room temperature), one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove layers from pans.
Let cool completely.

title: sharon's chocolate zucchini cake
directions: In bowl, cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk; blend.
Add flour, cocoa, baking soda and spices; mix well.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in glass pan or at 350° for 40 minutes in a metal pan.
No frosting required.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine Hawaiian Punch and fruit juices and water.
Stir well. Pour ginger ale and stir.
Float orange, lemon and lime slices.

title: never fail caramel icing
directions: Put brown and white sugar, cream and butter in saucepan. Bring to boil and let boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat immediately.
Add Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and enough powdered sugar to make it thick enough to spread.
Spread icing while it is still warm.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Beat well.
Add flavorings.
Sift baking powder with flour 3 times.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add to sugar mixture alternating with flour.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Spray pan with vegetable oil, then saute the mushrooms and green onion until soft.
Then add chicken and saute until done, about 5 minutes.
Blend chicken broth and flour and add to chicken mixture.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Stir in grapes and wine; heat through.
Serve over warm rice.

title: borschtsch ukrainsky
directions: Cook beef in bouillon. (The exact amount wasn't mentioned in the original recipe. I assume it should be "enough.") Cut beet roots, carrots, parsley and onions in strips; put them into another large pan. Add tomatoes or tomato puree, vinegar, sugar and a little bit of beef broth with lard (or 1 to 2 tablespoons butter). Cover with lid and cook for a while. Stir the vegetables from time to time. If necessary, add some more broth or water.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Drain water and add onion, butter, seasoning salt, pepper and cover with milk.
Cook until potatoes are tender and milk is hot.

title: marinade for beef or pork
directions: Blend in electric blender thoroughly and pour over 5 pounds beef or pork.
Marinate for only a few hours.
Excellent for barbecue.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add soda with flour.
Alternate milk and flour.
Add fruit and nuts.
Mix together.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes or until done.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put the popped corn into a large paper bag.
In a 4-quart bowl, mix all ingredients, except soda.
Cook for 2 minutes on High; stir.
Cook 2 minutes more on High.
Add the soda; mix well.
Pour into bag of popcorn; shake well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes; shake. Microwave 1 minute; shake.
Microwave 1/2 minute; shake.
Pour out and cool.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all spices together.
Works best if you mix dry spices in food processor or blender.
Add 4 teaspoons to each cup of hot water.

title: honey-baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion until onion is tender; combine with remaining ingredients in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 45 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spicy chicken pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: cheese and cherry pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Put Cool Whip in with cheese and sugar.
Place in graham cracker crust.
Place pie filling on top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash fruit; cut up apples and oranges.
Grind up all fruit. Add sugar and salt and set aside.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup of hot water.
Add 1 cup of cold water.
Mix with mixture and put in containers.
Freezes well.

title: * rio grande supper *
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Stir in corn, Cheez Whiz, barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with corn chips.
(Regular Cheez Whiz may be substituted.)
Serves 8.

title: zucchini-cashew quiche
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Prepare pie shell. Do not prebake. Sprinkle cashews in pie shell.
Slice zucchini and saute in melted butter until crisp-tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Layer on top of cashews.

title: beef-macaroni casserole
directions: I'm estimating on the garlic and chili powder because I don't normally measure them, I just stir some in, taste it and add more if I need it.
Also salt and pepper to taste.

title: one dish chicken and rice
directions: In large baking dish, combine all ingredients except chicken. Arrange chicken pieces on top.
May substitute chicken of your choice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done and rice mixture thickens.
Serve hot.
Makes a large dish.

title: corn in sour cream
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Stir corn, salt and sour cream into drippings.
Add bacon and heat through.

title: fettuccine with marinara
directions: For sauce, in medium saucepan cook onion, carrot and garlic in hot oil until tender, but not brown.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano, salt and dash of pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes or to desired consistency.
Cook pasta, drain well and serve with marinara sauce.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes in microwave.
Add peanuts and cook 5 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; cook 2 minutes.
Stir in soda.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Add salt to egg whites, beat until foamy.
(Beat only 6 at a time.)
Combine egg whites and sugar, continue beating until shiny, white, soft peaks form.
Put all all beaten egg whites together in a large bowl.
Beat yolks and vanilla until blended.
Fold into egg whites and add milk.

title: quiche
directions: Mix together eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Place ham, green pepper, onion and mushrooms in the pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over the top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Done when knife comes out clean.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Dumplings:
Sift flour in a large bowl.
Add shortening and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and mix with flour.
Add some cold water, a little at a time until dough becomes sticky.
Roll out dough and cut noodles as desired.

title: carol's brie cheese wheel
directions: Trim off top of Brie. Trim sides. Cover with caramel dip. Add apples in a circle around outer edge. Sprinkle on small pieces of apple, apricot and cranberries.

title: gouda strata
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Spread margarine on 1 side of each slice of bread.
Cut each slice diagonally into 4 triangles.
Arrange 16 triangles with margarine sides against sides and bottom of an ungreased square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.

title: beef roll(this recipe is similar to the pigs in a blanket recipe.)
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients together, except for the bacon and tomato sauce.
Shape the meat mixture into a roll about 2 to 3-inches long, and wrap bacon around each roll.
Hold together with a toothpick.
Place in a baking dish and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
(This dish may also be frozen, then cooked at a later date.)
Makes 12.

title: pork and zucchini stir-fry
directions: If possible, have butcher cut pork.
Saute with onion in oil over high heat until pork is lightly browned.
Add zucchini, mushrooms, marjoram, salt, pepper and bouillon.
Stir 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender and pork is thoroughly cooked.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add strawberries and finish filling freezer can with half and half.
Makes 1 gallon. Good stuff.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press with a fork dipped into flour to make cookies flat and the crisscross pattern on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Drain pineapple and cherries (if they are not drained well it will not make a ball). Mix cheese, pineapple and cherries.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: campers potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes (skins may be left on).
Peel and slice onions.
In a disposable foil 8 x 9-inch pan, layer potatoes, onions, butter, salt, pepper and paprika.
Place on charcoal grill with foil pan covered tightly with a piece of aluminum foil.
Grill for about 35 to 40 minutes until tender.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add sugar, flour, salt and pepper to can of corn. Beat egg yolks. Add milk and melted butter. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in egg whites. Pour into buttered baking dish. Set in hot water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set and lightly brown.

title: almond chicken
directions: Cut chicken in small strips.
Shake chicken in salt and flour. Saute in butter until chicken turns white.
Pour almond extract over chicken.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Add garlic powder, pepper and sauteed mushrooms to chicken.
Bring to a boil; cook over medium heat until liquid is reduced to half.
Add cream and heat through, but do not let boil.
Serve immediately over cooked rice.

title: applesauce cake with caramel frosting
directions: Melt oleo in large saucepan.
Add applesauce, white sugar and spices.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir in flour and soda.
Stir in egg. Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Heat butter; saute onions.
Add 4 cups water and boil until dissolved.
Add noodles; cook.
In another pan, put 2 cups water and the broccoli; steam.
Let come to a boil; add garlic powder. Cook 3 more minutes or until tender.
Add salt, 6 cups milk and very thin slices of cheese; stir and melt.
Do not let boil.
When all cheese is melted and soup is thoroughly hot, it is done.

title: onion beef burgers
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup. Mix until well blended.
Add 1/2 can of onion rings to mixture. Shape into 4 patties.
Broil on first side 9 minutes (4 inches from heat source); turn and boil on second side 5 minutes.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° until done.
Top with glaze.

title: baked berry pudding
directions: Mix together butter, milk, baking powder, sugar and flour to make a batter.
Spread in a greased deep baking dish.
Pour berries and boiling water over batter.
Bake at 400° until cake part is done (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).

title: golden turkey enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, 1/4 cup green onions, green chilies and salt.
Reserve 3/4 cup sauce.
Mix remaining sauce with turkey and 1/2 cup cheese.
Lightly fry tortillas in heated oil, one at a time.
While still hot, fill each tortilla with 1/8 of turkey mixture.
Roll; place seam side down in baking dish.
Combine reserved sauce with milk; pour over rolled tortillas.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining onions and cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook small beets until tender.
Cold dip and slip skins.
Make a pickling syrup of remaining ingredients.
Cover beets with mixture and simmer 15 minutes.
Seal in clean jars.

title: peach butter
directions: Blend peach skins in blender.
Cook with sugar; cook in crock-pot for a day.
Freeze in small jars or cans.

title: easy do maple syrup
directions: Mix the sugar, water, and corn syrup together. Bring to a boil. Stir constantly. Boil for 5 minutes Remove from heat and add maple flavoring.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together and drain.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer remaining ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spritzen
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour, stirring constantly until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs.
Spread on a cookie sheet that was greased.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool away from heat.
Mix cream cheese, pudding and milk, then spread on pastry shell.
Refrigerate for 2 hours, then spread Cool Whip on top and drizzle with Hershey's syrup.
Must be refrigerated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Melt butter; use half to put with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Put cooked broccoli in casserole dish; pour melted butter, next put cheese on top, then add crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon.
Set aside. In a saucepan, place the water, margarine, oil and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients, mixing well.
Set aside. Mix together the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to chocolate batter.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Start Chocolate Icing about 5 minutes before cake is done and frost cake in pan (batter will be thin).

title: potato salad
directions: Cooking Time: 15 to 20 minutes.
Servings: 4.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, powered sugar, Cool Whip together. Make pudding. When thick, fold into Cool Whip mixture. Put mixture in pan and top with Oreo crumbs and chill overnight.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: Wash and slice squash in thin slices.
Peel onions real thin and add to squash.
Cover onions and squash with water and salt; let stand 2 hours.
Drain.
Add celery salt, turmeric and mustard seed.
Bring to boil.
Heat 5 minutes.
Pack in jars.
Process 15 minutes in a boiling water bath.

title: caramel snappers
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
On it arrange pecans flat side down into groups of 4.
Place 1 caramel on each cluster of pecans.
Heat in slow oven (325°) until caramels soften, about 4 to 8 minutes. Watch carefully.
Remove from oven.
With buttered spatula, flatten caramels over pecans.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to waxed paper.
Swirl melted chocolate on top.
Makes 36 Snappers.

title: barbecued roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook roast until tender; cool.
Shred beef and place in saucepan.
Add sugar, broth, prepared mustard, catsup, liquid smoke and Worcestershire.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Serve warm on buns.
Melt cheese over beef, if desired.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Combine ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler. Add 1/3 cup cold water.
Beat well, then cook over rapidly boiling water, beating constantly, until mixture holds peaks when beater is raised, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat until spreading consistency, about 2 minutes.
Spread on cake.
Good on all cakes and jelly rolls.

title: ham strata
directions: Layer ham in pan.
Layer cheese on top of ham.
Layer bread cubes on top.
Sprinkle on mustard.
Sprinkle on flour.
In separate bowl mix milk and eggs.
Pour over top of layered mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown 30 to 45 minutes.

title: individual fat-free "fast" pizza
