directions: Make sure the pita is split in half.
Then spread 2 to 3 tablespoons spaghetti sauce on it.
Top with sprouts, mushrooms, onions and peppers to taste.
Put in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until heated through.
Enjoy!

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Boil chorizo.
While chorizo is cooking, remove stems from mushrooms.
Set aside caps.
Mince stems; set aside.
Once chorizo is cooked remove skin and mince.
In skillet, saute in a little of the butter the onions and garlic.
Add minced mushrooms stems and chorizo.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add parsley and wine.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add bread crumbs until forms stuffing.

title: berry mallow yam bake
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Toss 1 cup crumb mixture with yams (drained) and cranberries.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with miniature marshmallows.
Return to oven until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.
Good with turkey or ham.

title: cherry ice cream
directions: You will need a one-gallon ice cream freezer.

title: lite veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent roll dough into 13 x 9-inch pan coated with nonstick spray. Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until brown. Cool.

title: mccartney casserole
directions: Put all ingredients into a classroom.
Mix well, blending marvelous personalities.
Add 3 cups reading, 2 cups Math, 1 cup each:
Religion, Social Studies, Science, Health and Handwriting. Add 1/2 cup each:
Art, P.E., Music, Computers and Learning Center. Bring to a boil; turn off heat and let cool.
Next, add 3 tablespoons free time, 4 tablespoons outside play, 3 teaspoons parties and 2 teaspoons field trips and some wonderful class books written and illustrated by the McCartney Kids.
Put in a 22 x 22 casserole dish and bake for 180 days at full steam.
Sprinkle with laughter and fun.
Serve warm with a pinch of discipline and gallons of love!

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat until brown.
Drain it.
Put it into a casserole dish and add the hominy, cream of chicken and chili beans mixed in the hamburger meat.
Sprinkle the cheese over the top of this and add Fritos on top of the cheese; bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Happy eating.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cut bread in 1-inch slices and toast at 325° for 10 minutes. Cook onions and sugar 10 minutes in butter; stir in flour.
Add water, wine and broth; heat to boiling.
Reduce to low and simmer 10 minutes.
Put in ovenproof bowls.
Place bread slices and cheese on each.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix ingredients by spoon only, not electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: sopapillas
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening well.
Gradually add water, stirring with fork until it becomes crumbly.
On a lightly floured board, knead dough for a few minutes or until it is smooth.
Divide dough in half. Cover and let rise for 15 minutes.
Roll half the dough into a 12 1/2 x 10-inch rectangle.
Using a fluted pastry wheel, cut 2 1/2 inch squares from each half.
Don't reuse leftover dough.
Fry squares in hot oil for 35 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle powdered sugar and drizzle honey on top.
Serve while warm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs together with mixer at low speed. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix soup, sour cream, butter, onions and salt with potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Blend very well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Pour peas into a wire strainer and run hot water over them to thaw; drain well.
Combine in a bowl the peas, water chestnuts, celery, carrots and green onions.
Mix together the salad oil, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar, paprika, mustard, the 1/2 teaspoon salt and garlic.
Beat to blend and pour over pea combination.
Mix well and cover.
Chill for 30 minutes to an hour.
Shortly before serving, drain off any extra marinade.
Mix mayonnaise into salad; add salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange on salad leaves, garnish with bacon bits.

title: banana split cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make graham cracker crust as shown on box.
Mix 1 box vanilla instant pudding with can of pineapple (do not drain pineapple).
Mix 1 box of vanilla instant pudding with large Cool Whip.
Layer bananas, pineapple mixture, then Cool Whip mixture.
It will be 2 layers of each.
Decorate with cherries and chocolate syrup or nuts or graham cracker crumbs (leftover from crust).
Chill.
Bananas should be dipped in lemon juice to keep from getting browned.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan or 10 x 15 pan in the oven.
Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken; place skin side down on hot pan.
Bake 35 minutes; turn chicken.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until juices run clear.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Stem large mushrooms.
Chop stems with chopped onion, celery salt and some bread crumbs.
Spoon back into mushrooms.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine filling ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake an additional 40 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: brownies
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cook on top of stove.
Use deep skillet.
Use fresh sweet potatoes, sliced longways several times.
Put in skillet; add just enough water to cover.
Add salt, sugar, raisins and oleo or butter.
Cook until done.
Add cornstarch mixed with water.
Add vanilla.
Stir with fork lightly.
Let cook a minute.
You can add juice of an orange.

title: nana's orange julius
directions: Combine and blend 30 seconds in blender.
Serves 4 (8 ounce) glasses.

title: butterscotch goodies
directions: Melt the butterscotch morsels over low heat, stirring to keep from burning.
When melted, stir in peanuts and noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper; cool.

title: white sauce
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour milk mixture through a wire-mesh strainer into a small bowl, reserving the hot milk.
Melt butter in large skillet over low heat.
Add flour gradually. Cook, whisking constantly, 1 minute. Gradually whisk in hot milk and cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Whisk in whipping cream and remaining ingredients. Use immediately.

title: spam scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray casserole dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine soup, milk, pimientos and pepper.
In the casserole dish, layer half of each:
cubed Spam, onions, combined soup mixture, peas, potatoes; repeat layers.
Cover.
Bake 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Combine bread crumbs and parsley. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, covered, 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: steamed christmas pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
Sift flour, soda, spices and salt and add to egg mixture.
Dust fruit and nuts with flour and fold into batter.
Steam 3 hours and serve with hard sauce. Tin cans are good to steam in, then when you want to serve, remove bottom from can and push pudding out.

title: pea salad with bacon
directions: Prepare the dressing by combining the sour cream, mayo, parsley, dill and salt and pepper to taste.
Rinse the peas in hot tap water until defrosted; drain and chill.
Cook the bacon and chop up.
Mix all together with onions.
Serve on a lettuce bed.

title: corn chip casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with onion.
Add chili and tomato soup.
Simmer until well blended.
Line a casserole dish with corn chips.
Pour beef mixture over them.
Top with corn chip crumbs and then cheese.
Bake at 400° until the cheese melts.

title: m&m's meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 200°. Line baking sheet with parchment paper. In a medium bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy. Slowly beat in sugar until stiff, shiny peaks form. Fold in M&M's bits. Spoon 12 (2 to 2 1/2-inch wide) mounds onto prepared baking sheet. Garnish with M&M's bits, if desired, dotting tops. Bake 2 hours until dry and crisp. Turn off oven; let cool in oven 2 hours. Makes 12 meringues.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Drain artichokes and chop. Mix them and place in greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Scatter chilies on top.
Spread with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cortner's boiled custard
directions: Mix the pudding mix with a little of the milk by hand.
Stir in rest of milk, then beat 5 minutes with mixer.
Add sugar, cream and vanilla; beat with mixer 3 minutes or longer.
Pour into container to refrigerate.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: peach pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar.
Place peach halves in bottom of crust and pour egg mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until peaches are tender.

title: great guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until blended.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make into 2 patties.
Place in skillet with 1 teaspoon oil.
Brown on both sides.
Simmer on stove for 30 minutes. Drain off fat.
Add to the rest of tomato soup 1 teaspoon of mustard and finish can with water.
Pour over patties and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except apples, pineapple and nuts. Cook until thickened and let cool.
When cool, pour over apples, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.

title: yellow punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water. Mix everything but ginger ale. Add this when ready to serve.
Put crushed ice in punch bowl. Serves 50.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In 13 x 9-inch glass pan, place 8 slices bread, buttered side down.
Spread mushrooms, green pepper, cheese and bacon on top.
Place 8 more slices bread, buttered side up.
To eggs, add milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over casserole and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: cranberry poppy seed loaf
directions: Grease bottom of 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan; set aside.
In large bowl mix flour, sugar, poppy seed and baking powder; set aside.
Blend milk, margarine, egg product, vanilla and lemon peel; stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries; spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until done.

title: garlic whipped potatoes
directions: Wash and cut potatoes into 1-inch pieces.
Place in large saucepan and add cold water to cover.
Cover with lid and bring to a boil; cook 10 minutes.
Add garlic cloves and continue to boil 5 minutes.
Remove 5 tablespoons cooking water, reserve and drain potatoes.
Pass them through potato ricer or food mill.
Whisk in reserved water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Yields 2 servings.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix container of cottage cheese with dry jello. Add miniature marshmallows, pineapple and Cool Whip. Mix. Garnish top with sliced or whole strawberries. Serves 12.

title: fat-free dip mix
directions: Mix both ingredients together and chill.
Sprinkle some fresh parsley on top.
Great with vegetables or fat-free chips.
Good snack when on a diet.

title: hamburger broccoli pie
directions: Cook pie shells according to directions. Cook broccoli.
Brown meat.
In pot, combine meat, broccoli, soup, cheese, dash of garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour into 2 cool pie shells.
Top with cheese and put in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Mix next 4 ingredients into a separate bowl.
Add the 2 bowls together and roll out on wax paper which has been sprinkled with flour.
Roll about 1-inch thick.
Cut into circles of 1 1/2 to 2 inches.
Put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie roll, placing pieces close together on an ungreased pizza pan.
Bake cookie 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together, then spread on cookie.
Place sliced fruit of your choice in design on cream cheese.
Heat orange marmalade in small saucepan, then brush over fruits and edges of cookie as a glaze.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add milk, bread and vanilla. Pour mixture into a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until thickened.

title: tomato salad
directions: Cut an "X" on bottom of tomatoes and drop in pot of boiling water.
When the "X" starts to split, remove and drop tomatoes in cold water to stop cooking.
Slip the skin and core tomatoes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut; place in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Store, covered, in refrigerator for at least 24 hours before serving.

title: chess pie(9-inch)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat to mix.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch shell.
Bake about one hour or until knife blade inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: allison's goulash
directions: Brown the ground beef; cut up the onion and add to ground beef.
Add the 2 cans of tomatoes; add the jar of mushrooms.
Add the macaroni and cook this mixture until macaroni is done.
Add garlic salt, corn and beans.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: no brain dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, slice Twinkies in half lengthwise and place filling side up in pan.
Slice enough cakes to completely cover bottom of dish.
Layer banana slices over cakes.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Pour pudding over pineapple (make sure pudding is soft set).
Smooth Cool Whip over the pudding and sprinkle pecans over the top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Then spoon out and swear you slaved for hours!!

title: cajun ribs
directions: Brown ribs quickly in hot oil.
Mix remaining ingredients; put ribs in baking dish.
Pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be cooked on grill.
Use sauce for basting.

title: grandmother's christmas chow mein candy
directions: *These quantities may vary according to taste.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and brown in oil.
Push aside chicken; add onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook and stir a few minutes. Mix tomato paste with remaining ingredients and pour over chicken; stir well.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Uncover and cook until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: sugar-free cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all moisture has evaporated.
Mix all ingredients well and bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Add margarine to drained spinach.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
If mixture is too loose, add 2 tablespoons matzoh meal.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Mix cake mix, egg and margarine with fork.
Put mixture onto pizza pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Break broccoli into bite-size flowerets (not that much stem) and distribute evenly over bottom of dish.
Lay chicken breasts close together on top of broccoli.

title: layered mexican bean dip
directions: Arrange in order listed in square glass pan.

title: rotel potato casserole
directions: After potatoes have cooled off, slice with skins into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt the Velveeta with the Ro-Tel, onion and margarine in the microwave.
When melted, pour over potatoes. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: modified heidi potatoes
directions: Slice a thin slab off each side of baked potato.
Slice the slabs like thin French fries.
The remaining block can be cut in half, then quarters and eighths.
Cut to size of small French fries.
Put 2 cups water in bowl and add sugar.
Soak French fry size potatoes for 1 hour or more.
Pour off water and place potatoes in a flat baking dish.
Melt butter or margarine in a small pan.
Add chives, parsley and garlic powder.
Mix and pour over potatoes; cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done. Leave skin on potatoes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Drain cherry juice into saucepan.
Add sugar, cornstarch, butter, salt, almond flavoring and color.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Remove from heat, stir in cherries.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and top with ventilated top crust.
Bake 10 minutes in a 425° oven, then at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
I always use 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
I think it tastes more like fresh cherries.

title: watergate 7-up cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and Seven-Up and mix well.
Add nuts and coconut. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish jansons temptations(anchovies au gratin)
directions: Saute sliced onion in 2 tablespoons of margarine or butter. Peel potatoes and cut thin.
Butter 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Arrange 1 layer or half of amount of potatoes.
Spread onion and anchovy fillets over and top with remaining potatoes.
Sprinkle juice from anchovy can over potatoes and dot with remaining margarine or butter.
Add half and half and cover with aluminum foil.

title: chocolate bar pie
directions: Prepare chocolate crumb crust and set aside.
Break bar into sections.
Melt with milk and marshmallows in top of double boiler over hot water.
Stir constantly until smooth.
Cool to room temperature.

title: chicken capri
directions: Rub the breast with the cut lemon.
Squeeze the juice out as you rub.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over the chicken; coat with flour.
Heat butter in skillet; brown chicken breasts in butter. Mix the soup, sherry and cheese; pour over browned chicken. Simmer for about 1 hour.
Remove chicken to warm serving platter; spoon gravy over chicken.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven at 450°.
Combine the soup mix, the potatoes and the onion in a large bowl.
Stir gently, so that the vegetables are well coated with the soup mix.
Place the vegetables in a shallow baking dish that has been well coated with the spray.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally until the vegetables are tender and browned.
Makes 4 servings, 1 fat gram per serving.

title: double corn bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°. Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. In a large bowl, combine all the dry ingredients. Beat together the egg, milk and butter. Add the egg mixture, corn and sour cream to the dry ingredients. Stir just until blended. Do not overmix. Pour into the greased pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown and a toothpick comes out clean.

title: chinese barbecued spareribs
directions: Put
spareribs
on
a
baking sheet.
Slice meat between bones once
almost
through thickness.
Make sauce by crushing and blending
garlic
with
naam
yu sauce, sugar, salt and soy sauce and 5-Spice powder.
Rub
sauce
well
into both surfaces and cracks of meat.
Bake spareribs
in hot oven for 20 minutes on each side.
Allow meat to
attain
rich reddish brown color. When done, divide spareribs with knife.
Serve hot.

title: kuchen
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and butter and mix thoroughly.
Add egg and milk and blend well.
Press dough lightly into a greased square pan.
Cover with sliced fruit.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift and mix all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container in cool, dry place.
Mix 1/3 cup mix with 2/3 cup hot water.

title: lo-cal fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and chill; serve with your favorite cut up fruit:
cantaloupe, honeydew, strawberries, bananas, pineapple (fresh), apples, pears or grapes.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems and set aside caps.
Brown onion and garlic in olive oil.
Finely chop mushroom stems.
Add to onion and garlic and brown over low heat.
Combine onion, stems, egg, bread crumbs, cheese and parsley and mix.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Place mushrooms in baking dish or pan with soy sauce and water on bottom, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend dressing, cream cheese and deviled ham.
Stir in other ingredients.
Roll in crushed peanuts.
Makes one large or two small cheese balls.

title: percolator wassail
directions: Perk and let simmer for 20 minutes before serving.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Batter will be stiff and pour into a greased pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Arrange in layers in order listed using dressing between.
Top with cheese and bacon bits.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fudge cake brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo together and cool.
Add flour to eggs and sugar mixture, then the chocolate, oleo, vanilla and nuts. Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salmon hash
directions: Remove bone and black skin from
salmon.
Put 4 cups of water in a large skillet.
Add
all
the
ingredients and cook until onions are tender.
In a small
bowl, stir 3/4 cup flour into enough water to dissolve (stir
until
all lumps are out) and pour into skillet to thicken hash.
Cook a few minutes and stir to desired thickness.
Serve hot with biscuits.

title: polynesian stew
directions: Bring to boil or until meat is tender. Thirty minutes before serving, cut up small head cabbage. Turn up to medium or medium-high until cabbage is tender.

title: layered green salad
directions: In deep bowl, layer lettuce, onion, peas and cauliflower. Repeat layers 3 or 4 times. Spread Ranch dressing or mayonnaise evenly over top layer. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits. Best if made the night before.

title: one pot tuna pasta
directions: Bring water, bouillon cubes, pepper and basil leaves to a boil in a 4-quart pot.
Gradually add uncooked pasta so that water continues to boil.
Cover and simmer for 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: leche quemadaburnt sugar milk candy
directions: Roast pecans in microwave on a large glass plate on high for 8 minutes; stir and rearrange at 2 minute intervals.
Set aside.
In an 8 cup measure, melt margarine on high for 1 minute.
To margarine, add brown sugar and condensed milk.
Microwave on high for 7 minutes stirring at 2 minute intervals.
Beat until stiff. Add vanilla and pecans.
Spread in a greased 8 inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Sift
flour
and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Mix egg and milk; stir until well blended.
Knead lightly about 30 seconds on floured cloth.
Roll out very thin and cut into strips and allow to dry on board 30 to 40 minutes.
After cooked chicken is removed,
drop dumplings one at a time in broth.
If broth does not
cover
dumplings
add a little milk.
Cover and let simmer 20
minutes.
After
minutes cooking, place cooked chicken
on top to reheat.
Replace cover and continue cooking 10 minutes longer.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown
hamburger,
using
heavy
skillet.
Add onion and simmer until onion is barely tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 quart casserole and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: red beet chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Combine sugar, eggs and oil in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed, about 2 minutes.
Add beets, chocolate and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients, beating well.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pecan chicken(with wilted greens and pepper jelly chutney)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Line shallow baking pan with foil and lightly coat with cooking spray. Rinse chicken breasts and pat dry.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Blend cake mix and pudding mix together (dry), then add water, oil and milk and mix.
Add eggs one at a time and mix.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: slaw
directions: Bring vinegar mixture to boil, simmer for 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage, cover, and store in refrigerator over night.
Stir before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Put in 2-quart casserole with water.
Combine all dry ingredients in bowl. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes, then uncovered for last 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn; add other vegetables, ham and seasonings.
Coat with mayonnaise.
Serve chilled.

title: cherry pretzel dessert
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar and pretzels; reserve 1 cup crumbs for top.
Put remaining in a 9 x 13-inch pan; pat down.
Beat softened cream cheese; beat in powdered sugar.
Fold Cool Whip into cream cheese mixture.
Put 1/2 of cream cheese mixture on crust, then 1/2 of cherry pie filling.
Repeat cream cheese mixture and then cherries.
Put the rest of pretzel crumbs on top. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: bierax casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion. Drain grease and add cabbage; simmer for 20 minutes. Add seasonings the last 10 minutes. Layer 1 can of crescent rolls in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Put filling on top, then put cheese on top of meat. Add another layer of rolls. Bake until rolls on top are brown at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers and remove seeds.
Precook 5 minutes in boiling water.
Drain and sprinkle inside of peppers with salt. Cook ground beef and onions until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add salt, pepper, tomato juice, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer until rice is tender.
Cover peppers with tomato sauce and sugar; bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese as topping during last 15 minutes of baking time.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apricot bars
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, place apricots and enough water to cover. Heat to a boiling point.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes; drain.
Cool and chop; reserve.
Cut margarine into sugar and 2 1/2 cups Bisquick until crumbly.
Pat into ungreased 15 1/2 x 9 jelly roll pan.
Bake for 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Beat brown sugar and eggs; stir in apricots, 2/3 Bisquick, vanilla and nuts. Spread over crust.
Bake 30 minutes longer; cool and cut into bars, about 2 x 1-inch each.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: liver ribbons
directions: Cut calves' liver in thin ribbon like strips.
Put the oil in a heavy skillet and saute the sliced onion and wheat germ.
When the onion and wheat germ turn golden brown, add strips of liver. Saute for 3 minutes; sprinkle with salt.
Cover skillet for 1 minute before removing from the frying pan.
Yield: Serves 4.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients through ground beef.
On foil or wax paper, pat meat mixture into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on beef, leaving some beef showing on edges.
Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella over ham.

title: drop donuts
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together. Beat eggs; add applesauce and milk and add to dry mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in shortening (liquid or melted).
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into 370° oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix melted butter and brown sugar together.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll biscuits in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place biscuits in Bundt pan one layer at a time, sprinkling each layer evenly with nuts and butter/brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Turn out of pan while warm.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter, then nuts, then chocolate, then coconut, then pour Eagle Brand over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 15 minutes before cutting into bars.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine lemon juice with mayonnaise or salad dressing enough to moisten salad.
Steam rice according to package directions.
Do not overcook.
Cool.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill until served.
May be made a day ahead.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan or large casserole and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: cocktail sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, biscuit mix and cheese.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in a baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: spanish punch
directions: Combine ginger ale, pineapple juice and mashed strawberries in punch bowl.
Drop a few whole strawberries into punch bowl.
Keep iced while serving.

title: three-pepper baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a single layer in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish; sprinkle with salt.
In 10-inch skillet, cook and stir bell peppers and onion in oil until tender.
Stir in picante sauce and chili powder.
Spoon mixture evenly over chicken; cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; sprinkle chicken with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, just until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with cilantro, if desired.
Serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: venison steak
directions: Be sure to use ice water and don't overmix if you want a lovely and lacey crisp batter on the shrimp.

title: my favorite sandwich
directions: Toast the bread. Any kind will do, but fresh, homemade is best. Spread with Hellman's mayonnaise. Go to the garden and pick a tomato and a cucumber. Thinly slice the vegetables and layer on the bread. Top with alfalfa sprouts.

title: torta pascualina(argentine spinach pie)
directions: Cook, drain and finely chop spinach.
Saute onion in oil until tender.
Combine spinach, onion, nutmeg, oregano, salt, eggs and cheese.
Pour into pie shell.
Arrange top crust and seal.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Fold in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate bits and butterscotch bits, melted on warm heat.
Cool and cut into pieces as desired.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil fryer. Take meat off bones and cut or tear into small pieces.
Melt the margarine or butter and add 1 cup chicken broth and soup.
Mix well and pour over chicken.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Shred potatoes with smallest side of grater.
Add the egg and flour as needed for thickness.
Blend together.
Fry like you would a pancake. Sprinkle sugar on top and serve.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Combine and beat until fluffy.

title: mom's spaghetti
directions: Pour all cans into a large pot and break up tomatoes.
Add half of all the spices (can also add cut-up onion, garlic and green pepper, if desired).
Stir well and put on low heat.

title: microwave crusted stuffed turkey breast
directions: In a glass bowl, combine mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cover. Cook on High 4 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in the remaining stuffing ingredients with 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Place turkey breast, smooth side down.
Make horizontal cuts in thicker parts. With meat mallet, pound turkey to 14 x 9-inch rectangle.
Cover with stuffing mixture to within 1-inch of edges.
Fold short sides over.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Tie with kitchen string. Brush with mayonnaise.
Roll in crumbs.
Place, seam side down, in microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with paper towel.
Cook on High 10 minutes.
Cover ends of roll with foil and then paper towel. Cook on Medium 35 minutes or until internal temperature registers 170°, rotating dish after 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove string before slicing.

title: fruit and yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping, blending well.
Add fruit and spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes (or longer for softer texture) before cutting and keep chilled in refrigerator.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: taco platter
directions: On large platter, spread a little more than 1/2 bag chips. Saute onion.
Brown beef with onion; drain and add seasoning mix. Heat beans; spread beans on chips then put rest of chips on top of beans.
Spread meat mixture on top of that and cover with bag of cheese, next shredded lettuce.
Pour jar of salsa on top and spread evenly.
Spread chopped green onions.
Top this with sliced black olives.
Serve with sour cream.
(If needed heat in microwave just before serving.)

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake as per instructions.
When cool break cake into bite-size pieces.
Layer in punch bowl as follows:

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Completely thaw apple juice; stir in tapioca, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add butter and sliced apples.
Pour into pie shell; cover with a top crust or chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Chill before serving.

title: spicy glazed meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, cookie crumbs, onion, eggs, evaporated milk and seasonings.
Mix well. Turn into 1 1/2-quart loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Drain off drippings.
Cool for 5 minutes in pan. Unmold. Top with Peach Glaze.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Fill to line in ice cream maker with milk.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix dry jello with drained fruit.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
May add finely chopped nuts.

title: crock-pot venison sausage
directions: After cooked, simmer on stove (cut in small pieces), about 1/2 hour.
Add a little barbecue sauce to taste.
Serve over noodles.

title: meal in a muffin
directions: Mix first four ingredients and then add flour to mixture and stir to moisten flour.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Good with soup or salad.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs together until fluffy.
Add almond extract and sour cream.
Gradually add dry ingredients that have been thoroughly mixed together.
Refrigerate overnight and roll out on floured board and cut into shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Cream the butter and add finely crushed cookies.
Line pie pan with cookie mixture.
Place in fridge to chill.
Melt the marshmallows in milk over low heat and set aside to cool.
Beat the whipping cream.
Add liqueurs and blend.
Add the cream mixture to the marshmallow mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with shaved chocolate and chill overnight.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies and press 1/2 into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together.
In blender, mix milk, vanilla pudding and vanilla and add to cream cheese mixture.
Pour over pressed cookies and then add remaining cookies.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 20.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in blender for 5 minutes. Pour into ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Forms own crust.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix together. Set aside.

title: meat loaf in a loaf
directions: Cut a shallow slice 2 1/2 inches wide from top of loaf of bread.
Remove inside bread until sides and bottom are 1/2 to 1-inch thick.
Make 1 cup crumbs from removed bread.
Combine ground beef, egg, chili sauce, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.

title: glorified crackers
directions: Boil sugar and butter together for 3 or 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add nuts.
Pour over graham crackers which have been placed close together on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes in 325° oven.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Beat in milk and vanilla. Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg if desired.

title: deviled ham for chips
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer or fork until well mixed.

title: scramble
directions: Mix all ingredients in a very large roaster.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 8 quarts.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello according to package directions. Add the packaged strawberries, thawed.
Pour in pie crust and let set.
Before serving, add whipped topping and garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil, cooking 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Stir and mix well.

title: brownie drops(favorite christmas cookie ever since 1963)
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Cool.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Then add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat until thickened (5 minutes on medium speed).
Blend in chocolate.
Add flour and spices.
Then stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until cookies feel set when lightly touched, around 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly on sheet before removing.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: baked grits
directions: Combine and put in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° until firm.
Stir often.

title: tropical smoothee
directions: Combine all ingredients except sherbet in blender for 10 seconds.
Add sherbet and blend 5 seconds more.
Makes 2 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Blend 1/4
cup	sugar, 1 tablespoon flour, cinnamon and salt. Toss
lightly with apples.	Spoon into pastry lined pan or dish. Combine
butter,
brown
sugar
and
cup flour. Sprinkle over pie filling.
Cover with top crust and cut slits in top of crust. Bake at 425° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Stir in 1/2 cup each milk and melted butter.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Stir halfway through baking time.
May be made day before serving.
Bake 50 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325° or until warmed through. Serves 12.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into a loaf.
Cover lightly with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on thickness.
Bake in crock-pot 8 to 10 hours on low, 3 1/2 to 5 hours on high.
Tastes like taco in a loaf.

title: play dough(non-edible)
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook on low heat until like pie dough.
Knead dough.
Place in sealed container after cooled.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta; drain and pour in large mixing bowl.
Mix with the pasta the chopped vegetables.
Pour bottle of Italian dressing over the pasta and the vegetables.
Mix well.
Sprinkle Salad Supreme seasoning over the pasta mixture.
Season to taste.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours, then serve.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Cut zucchini in pieces; cook until tender.
Melt butter, mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour over zucchini in casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: In a shallow dish, combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge chicken.
In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Brown the chicken on both sides.
Remove and keep warm.

title: turkey cacciatore
directions: Cut turkey into small pieces.
Spray skillet with cooking spray, add turkey pieces and brown; set aside.
Add garlic, onion, green pepper and mushrooms to the pan.
Saute over high heat until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and oregano; simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to directions. Taste turkey mixture.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Sprinkle top with parsley.
Serve over portions of spaghetti.
Pass Parmesan cheese at the table.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter with sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add dark chocolate, vanilla, orange rind and milk.
Stir in coarsely grated zucchini.

title: oat dodgers
directions: Mix and
chill at least 5 hours.
Whip a few times with a spoon.
Place by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with spoon.
Bake
at
400° for 45 minutes, until light brown. Serve hot.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Stir in berry juice and cornstarch in bowl to dissolve cornstarch evenly.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Place filling in pie crust.
Can place solid top on strips.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix well and fold in a large bowl of Cool Whip (9 ounce). Pour in graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: beet salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and chill, then fold in the beets, celery and cucumber.
Mold in 8 small molds or one large mold.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan. Add brown sugar and boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk, stirring until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and cool.
Add confectioners sugar and beat well.

title: louisiana mud cake
directions: Melt margarine. Add cocoa.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and add sugar and vanilla, then add to cocoa mixture. Add flour and nuts. Pour into an 8 x 12-inch floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Stem and seed jalapenos and chop very fine. Combine with remaining ingredients. Chill. Serve with tortilla chips or serve on warm flour tortillas.

title: washington state apple pie
directions: In saucepan combine apples, water and lemon juice, cook over medium
low
heat
just until apples are tender.
Remove from heat
and
cool
(do not drain).
In large bowl, combine sugars, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt.
Add apples and
toss to
coat.
Place
bottom
pastry in pie plate.
Add apple mixture.
Cover with top pastry.
Seal and flute edges. Cut
slits in top crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat
Bake
35 to 45 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Cook meat and onions together.
In a large pan, mix Ro-Tel, beans and soups together.
Add meat and onion mixture.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: mushroom melody(serves 4)
directions: Brown and cook first 7 ingredients until meat is tender.
Add 1 large bag of small egg noodles.
Do not stir after putting in noodles.
Add 2 cups of water and cook over low heat until noodles are done.
Add about 8 slices of American cheese.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Beat in mixer bowl oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add all other ingredients; stir well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Wilt cabbage in large pot of hot water.
Mix ground meat, rice, egg, salt and pepper.
Line bottom of pot with the small cabbage leaves.
Put a large tablespoon of mixture in center of leaves and fold over one end; cover with water and tomato sauce. Simmer over low heat for one hour.
Put sauerkraut and tomatoes on top of rolls and simmer 45 minutes more.

title: non-edible play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add oil, water, food coloring and flavoring.
Cook 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Remove from pan and knead at once.
Be careful; it will be hot.
This dough can be kept in refrigerator in an airtight container for a long time.

title: mexican siesta casserole
directions: Mix all and put into casserole dish. Top with crushed Fritos, tortillas or Doritos and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until thoroughly hot and bubbly. Yum!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 of dried beef.
Form into ball and then roll onto remaining dried beef.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk until mixture is pasty.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat.
Cook until golden brown; drain.
Serve hot.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pecan cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs one at a time.
Mix this with dry ingredients.
Then fold in candied fruit and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: prune souffle
directions: Beat egg whites
until
very
stiff, add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat until
sugar
is mixed in and dissolved.
Fold in prunes.
Pour into a 9
x 13-inch baking dish and bake in a 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Turn
off oven after the 45 minutes but leave souffle in
oven
until
the
oven
cools.
Serve in squares.
Garnish with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Lay chicken in the bottom of dish.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° with foil on top.
Then remove foil and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: french silk pie
directions: Combine oleo and sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Stir in chocolate and flavorings.
Add eggs, one at a time.
After each addition, beat 5 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer. Pour mixture into baked pie shell; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Top with whipped cream; sprinkle with chopped pecans, if desired.

title: baked green peas
directions: Place alternate layers of peas, soup, onion, green pepper and celery in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Mix well and make into balls.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: butter crunch carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut into 1/4-inch diagonal slices.
In small saucepan, bring 1/2 cup water to a boil.
Add carrots; cover and cook until tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in almonds, brown sugar and lemon pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly for 3 minutes or until sugar dissolves.
Add cooked carrots; toss to coat.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange rolls
directions: Stand the biscuits on edge in a greased Bundt pan.
Heat the butter, sugar and orange rind.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn out of the pan at once.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind apple, cranberries, celery, pecans, orange, and pineapple.
Chill.
Mix Jell-O and sugar; add boiling water mixed with unflavored gelatin.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Pour into a large mold.

title: kris kringles
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup, in 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and mix in cereal.
Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Let harden.

title: goodies
directions: Melt almond bark and add chunky peanut butter, peanuts marshmallows and Rice Krispies.
Spoon out on wax paper.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: 5 bean salad
directions: Mix beans and vegetables in colander; drain.
Heat remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour mixture over vegetables and mix well in large bowl.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Serve cold.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pretzel jello salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crush pretzels with rolling pin.
Place in bowl and add melted margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and press along sides and bottom. Bake for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: cucumber and rye
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing together.
Spread on party rye bread.
Top with slice of cucumber.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: vegetable macaroni
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, gradually stir soup into creamed cheese. Add milk, mustard and pepper.
Over low heat, heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Add macaroni, vegetables and Parmesan cheese. Heat through.
Stir often.

title: diabetic mile high apple pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, Equal, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Sprinkle over apples in a large bowl and toss. Arrange apple mixture in pie crust. Bake in a preheated 425° oven until pastry is golden and apples are tender, 40 to 50 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Bake in 350° oven 1/2 hour.
Turn and cook 1/2 hour on other side.
Double recipe for 8 or more chops.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in frying pan and drain the fat.
Arrange rice and sausage meat in alternate layers with onion.
Pour on undiluted tomato soup.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: laurice's baked beans
directions: Bake 2 1/2 hours, uncovered, at 325°.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook onions, celery, broccoli and water in saucepan over medium-high heat 10 minutes, until broccoli is tender.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in butter, salt and milk.
In bowl, mix flour and milk.
Stir into soup, a few tablespoons at a time, allowing time for it to warm and thicken the soup.

title: jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and cream; stir.
Put in mold and let set; remove and put on plate.
Real delicious.

title: souper meat 'n potato pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs and seasoning. Press firmly into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Spoon off fat.
Frost with potatoes.
Top with remaining soup and cheese.
Garnish with cooked sliced bacon.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, coconut and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by spoonfuls 1-inch apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to a wire rack to cool. Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar, then add eggs and beat well. Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add mashed bananas to mixture.
Next, add dry ingredients gradually.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold consomme, then heat until dissolved. Cool mixture and add chopped cheese.
Beat until well blended. Cool to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until ready to serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peach crisp
directions: Pour all of the peaches and syrup into a well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches.
Sprinkle coconut and then nuts over cake mix.
Pour melted oleo over all and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly around edges.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In large bowl, combine Rice Krispies and powdered sugar.
Melt peanut butter and margarine, then pour over Rice Krispies mixture. Mix thoroughly, then form into firm 1/2 inch balls.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: gazpacho(spanish meatless soup)
directions: In food processor fitted with steel blade, puree first 11 ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours.
Serve with remaining ingredients in separate bowls as garnishes.
Tabasco may be made available, too.
Serves 4.
Spanish soup.

title: scratch beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, keeping melted butter aside to pour on batter after it is poured into 2 small or 1 large loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until browned.
You may indulge in the remaining case while your bread cooks.
Bread makes excellent bologna sandwiches.

title: mandalay chicken
directions: Shake chicken in mixture of flour, curry powder and salt. Brown lightly in oil in skillet.
Remove chicken and place in large baking dish.
Stir together sugar, bouillon, apricots, onion, water, lemon juice and soy sauce.
Pour over chicken. Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350° or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken to serving dish.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons of cornstarch, dissolved in water, to sauce to reach desired thickness.
Serves 4.

title: meat and potato soup
directions: Brown and drain ground meat.
Put all ingredients, except milk, in large pot with meat.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in milk and cook until hot.

title: warm sauce for cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Stir constantly over medium to low heat until sauce is slightly thickened.
Pour heated sauce over slices of pound cake and serve.

title: johnny's french toast breakfast for mom
directions: Mix egg, milk, Sweet 'N Low and vanilla in bowl.
Dip bread in mixture.
Fry in skillet sprayed with Pam.
Serve on toast the syrup and butter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream thoroughly.
In a casserole dish, put in half of broccoli and then half of soup mixture, then another layer of each.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wedding punch(non-alcoholic)
directions: Make syrup by boiling 4 cups sugar and 4 cups water for 10 minutes.
Add tea and fruit juices and water.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Right before serving, add the ginger ale and strawberries.
Pour over block of ice or crushed ice.
Serves 60 to 70.
This punch is always a "hit" at weddings.
I think it is the best.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients and set aside. Combine the first 5 ingredients, then add dry mixture.
You might want to refrigerate dough.
Take a small piece of dough and roll it between hands to form a rope.
Place the rope in the shape of an object on a foil-covered cookie sheet.
Crush suckers and fill your shapes.
Bake at 350° for 4 to 6 minutes.
Cool and remove from foil.
Merry Christmas!

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: In bowl, blend first 6 ingredients; whisk in olive oil and pepper.
Place chicken in shallow non-aluminum bowl and cover with marinade.
Refrigerate 8 hours, turning once.
Grill chicken over hot coals, 4 minutes each side.
Serves 6.

title: egg-mushroom breakfast casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in rice, mushrooms and cheese.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Cut into squares and serve immediately.

title: plain roll dough
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water.

In a large bowl, combine sugar, shortening and salt. Stir in hot milk. Cool to lukewarm. Add softened yeast, egg and 2 cups of the flour; beat well. Gradually add remaining flour or enough to make a soft dough. Cover and let rise in a warm place until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down. Shape into rolls.
Makes about 24 hot rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemony light cooler
directions: In pitcher, combine grape juice, sugar and ReaLemon.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add club soda and fruit.
Serve over ice.
Recipe makes about 7 cups and can easily be doubled.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all and add butter the size of a walnut.
Pour into well-buttered pan and sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Bake in a 350° oven, uncovered until set.

title: boston sandwich spread
directions: In a medium bowl mash beans.
Add next 3 ingredients; blend well.
Spread between slices of bread.

title: martha washington candy(peanut butter roll)
directions: Mix 2 pounds confectioners sugar, margarine, milk and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Mix with hands until well mixed and smooth. You may have to add extra sugar until consistency to roll.
Roll dough on surface that has been dusted with confectioners sugar to desired thickness.
Spread peanut butter over entire surface and roll like jelly roll.
Cut roll in half and place on flat tray. Cover with Saran Wrap and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the two packages of thawed strawberries. Prepare cake mix as directed.
Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with marshmallows.
Pour cake mix batter over marshmallows. Spoon strawberry mixture over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.
Store in refrigerator.

title: walnut wonder cake
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla and beat.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with sour cream set aside.
Combine brown sugar, white sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Spread half the butter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle half the sugar and nut mixture over first layer.
Repeat layer of batter then sugar and nut mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: karo crazy crunch
directions: Put corn and nuts on a cookie sheet.
Combine sugar, butter and syrup in a 1 1/2-quart pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns a light caramel color.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Spread over popcorn and nuts.
When hard, break in pieces and store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: cobb salad(makes 2 servings.)
directions: Spread chopped lettuce evenly over bottom of a shallow medium-large salad bowl.
Arrange ingredients in rows over lettuce with minced chicken in a narrow strip down center, tomato, Blue cheese and avocado on one side and green onion, egg and bacon on other side.
To delay serving, toss minced avocado in lemon juice to prevent darkening.
Cover salad with a damp paper towel; refrigerate.
Before serving, add oil and vinegar dressing and pepper to taste.
Toss at table.
Serve on chilled lettuce-lined plates.

title: hound dogs
directions: Use oblong microwave dish.
Line hot dogs in dish, going in the same direction.
Prepare mashed potatoes (instant works best) to serve 6 to 8. Pour over the hot dogs.
Then place a layer of cheese on top of the potatoes.
Place in microwave on High for 5 minutes. Cheese should be melted and dish heated through.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, crushed crackers, salsa or picante sauce, egg, onion and green pepper in large bowl until thoroughly combined.
Form into loaf and place in a baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 375°.
Reduce heat to 350° and sprinkle with shredded cheese; bake an additional 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Remove from pan and slice.
Garnish slices with salsa or picante sauce.

title: five decker dinner
directions: Cut bacon into 1 inch pieces and line the bottom of a skillet. Shape hamburger into patties and place on top of bacon.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
On top of this place sliced onion, potatoes and carrots in order.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper. Place parsley on top layer and sprinkle with celery salt.
Cook on medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup water and cover.
Cook on low heat for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: This is a colorful salad for a luncheon or at Christmastime.

title: filling for pork chops
directions: Mix apples, raisins, crumbs, salt and sugar.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add to apple mixture.
Sprinkle with hot water; mix well.

title: salami
directions: Mix well. Wrap in foil forming a tube. Poke holes with toothpick. Lay tubes on rack over pan with water. Bake 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool. Remove foil and wrap in plastic wrap. You may freeze this.

title: microwave cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, saving 1/3 of tomato soup.
Pack mixture into a glass loaf pan.
Spread remaining soup on top. Cover with wax paper.
Cook at power level 7 for 23 to 29 minutes, rotating dish after 12 minutes.
Check for doneness after 23 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: In hot oil, fry garlic and onion until soft; add beef.
Cook until browned.
Mix in salt, pepper, tomato paste blended with hot water and crumbled rosemary leaves.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or a Bundt pan. Beating by hand, cream butter and sugar.
Mix in one egg at a time.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs.
Add milk, coconut and nuts. Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan snowballs
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat first four ingredients until creamy. In separate bowl, add flour, oats, pecans and salt.
Add to creamy mixture and mix well.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 15 to 18 minutes, or until bottom is golden brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Reroll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg well.
Add apples and nuts. Stir together dry ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: santa rosa pie
directions: On serving plate, spread beans into pie shape 8 to 9-inches in diameter.
Cover with avocado dip.
Combine olives and green onions.
Spread over pie.
Mix chilies and tomato.
Spread on top. Cover with cheese; frost with sour cream and spread sauce over top.
Serve with home-fried flour or corn tortilla chips.

title: power cookies
directions: Cream together the brown sugar, white sugar, butter and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and soda and beat into first mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Let cookies cool one minute and remove from pan.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: authentic indian fry bread(from the ute indians of arizona)
directions: Heat oil to 360° in heavy 5-quart pan.
In a large bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually stir in 1 cup water. Knead dough until it is no longer sticky.
Cover.
Let it stand 15 minutes.
Pull off 2-inch balls of dough, roll each on a lightly floured surface into circle 1/4-inch thick.
Pierce dough several times with a fork.
Deep fry the circles, 2 or 3 at a time until bottom of each is a golden brown.
Turn and cook 1 or 2 minutes more.
Makes 12 pieces.
Serve warm with honey, syrup or powdered sugar.

title: butternut squash pie(pumpkin)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake 15 minutes at 425°; then 20 minutes at 350° or until filling thickens.

title: thank you casserole
directions: In large skillet brown ground beef and drain grease.
Cut onion into small pieces.
Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Layer potatoes, ground beef, onion and soups in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together and roll into balls and brown in skillet.
Remove balls and make gravy.
Put flour in drippings as for milk gravy only use water.
Add mushroom soup.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine margarine, eggs, flour and cottage cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Add spinach.
Cut velveeta in cubes and mix into casserole dish with other ingredients.
Brown bread crumbs and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and molasses and mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Make into balls.
Roll in sugar; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 370° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add onion. In a large pot, add all ingredients to meat. Add enough water for the consistency you would like. Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Good served over Doritos or cornbread.

title: overnight pineapple cake
directions: Mix crackers, nuts and baking powder.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg whites, adding sugar gradually until thick.
Add vanilla. Fold in cracker mixture.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 300° until lightly brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: turkey pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups stuffing mix with 1/4 cup butter in bowl, mixing well.
Press into bottom and side of 9-inch pie plate. Blend soup and milk in saucepan over low heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add turkey, peas and pepper, mixing well. Spoon into stuffing shell.
Roll 3/4 cup stuffing into fine crumbs.
Combine with 1/4 cup butter, mixing well.
Spoon around rim of pie plate in border.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until browned and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings, about 335 calories each.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix together and store in airtight containers.

title: aunt pearle's cocoa cream pie filling
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, corn starch, egg yolks, and salt together. Add milk and vanilla, stir. Cook in a double boiler until mixture is thick.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add eggs, add bread crumbs and tomato sauce.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter or oleo.
Add to meat.
Add Tabasco sauce, salt and seasoned salt.
Mix well.
Spread out in baking pan. Shape to loaf.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes, longer if you want it well done.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Cook to hard-crack stage.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 or 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon oil.
Give a quick stir and step back.
Pour into large cookie sheet and let set until hard.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Bring to boil; melt peanut butter. Combine with sugar and syrup mixture.
Pour over cornflakes.
Mix rapidly.
Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: In a saucepan dissolve brown sugar, mayonnaise and barbecue sauce.
Then take water chestnuts with a 1/2 strip of bacon.
Wrap bacon around chestnuts. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Drain off grease.
Pour sauce over water chestnuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix oleo, eggs and Karo together.
Add flour, sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: edible peanut butter clay
directions: Mix ingredients in medium-size bowl until dough is smooth. Let kids form mixture into bunnies, lizards, monsters and other creations.
They can then decorate their edible artworks with peanuts, raisins, chocolate chips, etc.
Makes about 10 creatures, depending on sizes.
Store unused dough in refrigerator.

title: creamed ground beef and cabbage
directions: In skillet, brown meat and onion in margarine.
Add cabbage and the dry ingredients, then the milk.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. You can make a white sauce with the milk and flour instead and add it to the meat mixture, if you'd rather.

title: chili
directions: Add ingredients to hamburger after browned and drained; simmer 20 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar very well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with milk.
Remove 1/2 cup of the berries and crush with a fork.
Stir into the batter.
Add remainder of berries and mix gently by hand.
Fill greased muffin cups 7/8 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.
Yield:
16 muffins.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Beat pudding and milk as directed on pudding box; fold in Cool Whip.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prepare pie crust.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate.
Cool.
In large bowl, cream butter. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Blend in cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at medium speed for 5 minutes after each addition.
Pour into cooled pie crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: best ever rolls
directions: Pour yeast over warm water and sugar.
Let set.
Pour boiling water over butter or margarine; stir until butter melts.
Add 2 eggs, salt and sugar; mix well.
Add 4 to 5 cups flour, one at a time.
Stir until blended.
Dough will be sticky.
Put 1/2 cup flour on board; knead until flour is gone and dough is not sticky. Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise 1 hour.
Punch down; let rise 1 hour more.
Punch down; make into rolls.
Let rise. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses and salt. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Make into small balls.
Roll in sugar and place on baking sheet.
Do not flatten. Bake at 350°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix and sift sugars.
Add to shortening, peanut butter, eggs, milk, milk chocolate chips and vanilla as desired.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mom's clam chowder
directions: Peel, dice and cook potatoes until tender.
Set aside.
Saute onion, then add clams, milk, cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Add potatoes.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Garnish with Tabasco sauce, if desired.
May use fat-free cream cheese.

title: peach chutney
directions: Chop peeled peaches, onions, garlic and raisins.
Add one half of the vinegar.
Cook until soft.
Add all other ingredients. Cook until thick.
Pour into hot jars.
Seal at once.

title: molasses cake
directions: Heat molasses and shortening in a small pan (do not let boil). In another bowl, combine dry ingredients and pour in molasses mixture and stir.
Add eggs and boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chewy chess brownies
directions: Heat butter and brown sugar on low heat.
Remove and add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13 pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle top with some confectioners sugar.
Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients to form a stiff dough.
Form the dough into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
These are nice for Christmas.

title: pea casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soup, water chestnuts and milk together. Drain peas and add to mixture.
Place in greased casserole dish and crumble crackers on top of casserole.
Put pats of margarine on top and cook for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Whip sweet potatoes with butter.
Mix with white sugar, cream, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add crushed pineapple to sweet potatoes. Pour into baking dish (about 10-inch dish).

title: crazy crust cherry pie
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine flour, sugar, water, shortening and egg.
Blend well at lowest speed.
Spread batter into a 9 or 10-inch pie pan (deep dish).
Carefully spoon pie filling into center of batter.
(Do not stir.) Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: highland shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture, one cup at a time.
Prick all over with a fork.
Place in a preheated 375° oven and immediately reduce heat to 300°.
Bake for 1 hour until pale golden brown.
Cut in fingers while hot.
Cool in pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Add oil, walnuts, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the syrup and sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add Special K cereal. Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: italian spinach bread
directions: Spread mixture over split loaf of Italian or French bread. Heat in oven after wrapped in tinfoil.
Heat until cheese melts. Top with Parmesan cheese before heating.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and dry pudding mix.
Add nuts, marshmallows and pineapple.
Mix together and put in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Make a "well" and add remaining ingredients.
Fill pans 2/3 full.
Use regular size loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350°.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Good dressing for salad plate of sliced apples, oranges and kiwis on lettuce bed.
Drizzle nicely over fruit.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar in a Ziploc bag.
Cut each biscuit in half. Place 8 pieces of biscuit dough at a time in bag and shake to coat.
Layer pieces in a Bundt pan.
Melt the butter or oleo. Add remaining cinnamon and sugar into it.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a greased Bundt pan.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar 1/2 cup at a time; add eggs, one at a time.
combine
flour
and	salt;
add
small amount at a time. Add buttermilk.
Batter
should
look
like
a cake mix that needs more flour.
Cook
in unbaked pie shell at 300° for 1 1/2 hours until pie is golden brown.

title: salmon pate
directions: Mix ingredients well; shape into a loaf.
Top with parsley flakes, if desired.
Excellent on Ritz, Town House, etc., crackers.

title: beer cheese spread
directions: Grate both cheeses and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients to form smooth paste.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Best prepared about 24 hours before using.
Great on Triscuits.

title: quick mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix milk and flour and beat two minutes.
Add mayonnaise to mixture.
Put into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: georgetown broccoli pecan(4 servings)
directions: Trim broccoli flowerets into 1/2-inch buds.
Trim off tough ends and discard.
In a wide skillet or wok, heat oil.
Add the garlic and pecans.
Saute until pecans are lightly browned 2 to 3 minutes.
Lift pecans from oil with slotted spoon.
Drain and set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender with 1 medium onion, 2 sticks celery, salt and pepper.
Cool.
Skin and debone chicken.
Cut into pieces and spread
chicken
in
bottom
of
x 13-inch baking dish.

title: large pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 items together. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each one. Sift flour and baking powder together. Add flour, then milk. Mix well, then more flour and milk. Mix well. Keep alternating until all flour and milk is used (start with flour and end with flour). Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°. START IN COLD OVEN. Use favorite icing or eat plain.

title: swedish pancakes with lingonberry sauce
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Add half the milk.
Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Stir into the egg mixture.
Add remaining milk, cream and butter.
Bake in large cakes on hot griddle.
Place sauce on the cake; roll up and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Or bake silver-dollar size; top with sauce and sprinkle with sugar.

title: moist banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: california chicken soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine all ingredients, except tortellini and broccoli.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 25 minutes. Add broccoli and tortellini; simmer 10 minutes or until broccoli and tortellini are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve hot.

title: three-day coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8 or 9-inch layers.
When layers are completely cool, split in half.

title: cherry streusel coffee cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients with the milk.
Spread 3/4 of the batter in greased pan. Spread on pie filling. Spoon on rest of batter.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix lard, sugars, eggs, soda, vanilla, baking powder, flour and salt until well mixed.
Stir in oatmeal, Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: heavenly banana pudding
directions: First put down a layer of vanilla wafers, then a layer of sliced bananas with layer of whipped cream.
Repeat as many layers as you like.
Chill.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line bottom of plastic cold cut keeper with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Spread a layer of pudding over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Top with a layer of chocolate frosting.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Peel and slice melons, tangerines and bananas.
Starting with honeydew melon, add other fruits and melons, layer by layer, leaving several strawberries for top layer.
Keep cool until served.
Make according to number to be served.

title: best pound cake
directions: Blend together with hand mixer the liquid Butter Buds, sugar, Egg Beaters and vanilla.
Alternate adding a little flour and then a little milk.
Keep alternating until you have added all the flour and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a Bundt pan sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pat-a-pie crust
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Combine cooking oil and cold milk; add to flour mixture.
Stir gently and pat thinly into a 9-inch pie plate, building up top edge.
Flute edge; fill and bake according to recipe directions.
Or for a baked shell, prick crust.
Bake at 450°
for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 1 crust.

title: golden carrot raisin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine orange juice and enough ice cubes to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Add juice-ice mixture to gelatin; stir until thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice and stir in carrots and raisins.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 4.

title: easy steak and gravy
directions: Roll steak in seasoned flour and brown in skillet until brown. Put in crock-pot.
Add water.
Cook for 8 to 10 hours.

title: cheddar cheese biscuits
directions: Mix 5 ingredients until blended.
Work in flour and last buttermilk. Drop by teaspoons onto tin. Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 350° until golden (15 minutes).

title: cranberry mold salad
directions: Prepare jello according to directions and chill until slightly thickened.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add all ingredients (including jello) and chill until firm.
(I substitute pineapple juice for water in jello.)

title: corn lite bread
directions: Mix and bake in 2 small greased loaf pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then increase heat to 450° for 10 more minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Serve sliced.

title: broccoli blue cheese fettucine
directions: Steam broccoli until just tender, then chop.
You should have about 2 1/4 cups.
Melt butter in a large skillet; add garlic, green onions and broccoli.
Saute for 3 minutes.
Stir in cream, salt and pepper and cook to a gentle boil until sauce thickens slightly.
Toss sauce with hot pasta in a serving bowl.
Add Blue cheese and toss to distribute evenly.
Add Parmesan cheese and toss again.
Serve immediately with extra grated cheese and pepper on the
side.
Serves 4.

title: little quickies with hamburger meat
directions: Scramble hamburger meat in a skillet; add onions and brown. Drain off grease.
Pour in pork and beans.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve with potato chips and salad.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well. Cook egg, sugar and vinegar until thick. Add butter and let cool.
