Tear marshmallows in small pieces.
Cut pineapple in small pieces. Whip the cream.
Add cream, eggs, vinegar and sugar to other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator to cool.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Cook tomatoes and juice, brown sugar, butter, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil; thicken with cornstarch (dissolved in 1/4 cup water).
Bake in shallow baking pan with foil cover about 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil.
Add crumbs and cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot and spicy rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in ovenproof casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat thoroughly at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey tortilla roll-ups
directions: Lay out tortilla.
Spread on cream cheese.
Place meat and cheese on top.
Roll up.
Cut in 1-inch slices and poke with toothpick.
Serve warm or cold.
Warm at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, cinnamon and salt in thick skillet; cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture blends and bubbles.
Arrange carrots in skillet.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes over low heat.
Uncover; cook about 15 minutes, basting often until carrots are glazed.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine cooked rice, milk, raisins, Sego milk, sugar, vanilla, butter, eggs and nutmeg.
Bake at 325° until custard-like, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: onion calaste(casserole)
directions: Melt margarine	in
skillet;
add
onions and cook low, stirring often,
covered,
to
minutes
or until soft. Spoon into	casserole
dish;
spread
cheese over and sprinkle with pepper.
Heat	soup
and
milk
in same skillet, stirring constantly until
smooth.
Pour
over onion and cheese layers. Stir slightly with tip of knife to let sauce flow to bottom of dish.
Overlap
bread
slices
into ring on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bread is toasted and sauce bubbly.

title: fat-free devil's food cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and soda.
In another bowl, whisk together egg whites, water and syrup.
Add dry ingredients to this and pour into either a 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 8-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes to 40 minutes with an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place sauce and cheese in middle of tortillas.
Roll.
Add remaining sauce and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond slices
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Grease cookie sheet pan. Shape dough into loaves 1/2-inch in diameter, on cookie sheet.
Brush tops with beaten egg.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool and cut diagonally.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, Miracle Whip, Worcestershire sauce, onion, garlic and celery salt.
Blend until smooth.
Cover and chill. When firm, form into ball.
Roll ball in dried beef and parsley. Cover and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: dill muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, flour and dill.
Stir in sour cream.
Spoon in small muffin tin, filling 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 18.

title: tomato-basil pie
directions: Put pie crust into a 9-inch pie plate.
Flute edges.
Bake pie crust according to directions.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese on bottom.
Let cool.
Put tomatoes wedges on top of cheese.
Put basil and garlic in food processor.
Sprinkle over tomatoes.
Mix remaining Mozzarella cheese, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, and pepper.
Spoon this cheese mixture over basil.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Add water to potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Make white sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add ham and undrained vegetables.
Heat; do not boil. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: new testament pottage
directions: Cover lentils with 2 cups boiling water, cool and drain.
Fry garlic with onions in oil.
Add cumin and coriander.
Add drained lentils.
Stir in well and add ham hocks and celery salt plus bay leaves.
Cover with 1 quart of water and simmer for 2 hours tightly covered.
Remove ham hocks.
Cut off rind (outer skin) and finely chop meat and put into the lentils.
Add nonfat dried milk to taste.

title: easy microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart casserole dish that can be used in the microwave.
Microwave at High for 5 minutes. Stir in peanuts.
Microwave 2 to 5 minutes, stirring after 2 and 4 minutes, until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned.
Stir in butter, vanilla and baking soda until light and foamy.
Spread on a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet that has been well buttered, to a thickness of 1/4 inch.
Let cool, then break into pieces.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in ovenproof pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk. Pour into melted butter.
Add any fruit into middle of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot or on low heat in large saucepan.
Cook on low until cream cheese is melted.
Keep warm. Serve with sliced French bread.
This is everyone's favorite hors d'oeuvre.

title: eagle brand cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in real lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill three hours or until set.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pie pan spinach
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pastry with fork.
Bake 3 minutes in 400° oven.
Prick again where necessary.
Bake 5 more minutes. Cool completely.
Drain spinach well and set aside.
Cook bacon in large skillet.
Remove and reserve, leaving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Work in shortening.
Add milk and mix well.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half until 1/4-inch thick. Divide sausage in half and spread evenly over dough.
Roll each into a roll.
Slice and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix
pudding
and
milk;
fold in sour cream, then Cool Whip. Slice
and
fold
in bananas.
Place layer of wafers in bottom
of container.
Pour
layer of mix over wafers; repeat ending with pudding.
Crumble a few wafers over top; refrigerate.

title: turkey breast marinade
directions: Mix all together.
Marinate for 1 hour in fridge.
Grill.

title: braunschweiger ball(appetizer)
directions: Mix at room temperature.
Chill until you can form into ball. Roll in parsley flakes.
Serve with crackers.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in large skillet. Drop mixture by tablespoon and fry until golden brown.
Drain (serve hot). These can be frozen after frying and reheated in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water in double boiler, about 20 minutes, until thick.
Add cheese and butter while hot. Add salt, paprika and slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into casserole and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: touchdown taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spread bean dip on bottom of a small baking dish.
In a bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, taco seasoning, and garlic.
Pour over bean dip.
Spread shredded cheese over mixture.
Bake 15-20 minutes.
Top with tomatoes, onion, and olives.
Service with tortilla chips.

title: upside down meat pie
directions: In 10-inch ovenproof skillet, brown beef and cook celery, onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir to separate meat; drain well. Stir in soup and mustard.
Combine biscuit mix and water.
Roll or pat dough into a circle slightly smaller than skillet.
Top with biscuit dough.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until browned.
Turn upside down on platter.
Top with cheese.
Cut in wedges and serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix together and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until firm.
Place on sandwich buns.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg, water and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to batter; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges of cookies are light brown.
Cool in pan for several minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yield:
48 servings.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp and chop. Reserve shell.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil; saute onion.
Mix in pulp. Cook 5 minutes; add beef.
Cook until no pink remains.
Mix in seasonings; stuff shell.
Arrange in oiled baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic.
Drain off grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: chicken salad delight
directions: Mix everything except salad dressing and Cool Whip together. Bland salad dressing and cool Whip together, then mix it with everything else.
Place on a bed of lettuce and serve with assorted crackers of your choice.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, sugar and oil. Add mashed bananas, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 80 minutes.

title: soda pop cake
directions: Blend cake mix, soda pop and eggs until moistened, then beat as directed on package.
To deepen color, add food coloring.
Pour batter into a floured and greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Use any frosting you wish.

title: date balls
directions: Mix together and cook butter, egg, dates and sugar for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and cereal; mix.
When cool enough to handle shape into balls and roll in either coconut or confectioners sugar.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 7 ingredients.
Add flour, then chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 48.

title: golden brown peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together.
Gradually add the sugar and cream thoroughly.
Add the egg, then the flour. Form into the balls and place on a lightly greased baking pan. Flatten with a fork dipped into flour.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: beef or pork marinade
directions: Mix together and marinate at least an hour.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle brown and white sugar mixed with cinnamon over batter. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl and pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Combine biscuit mix, sour cream and milk in a bowl. Spread this over chicken mixture, all the way to the edges. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice eggplant and brown a little in skillet with 1 stick of butter.
Rotate in casserole dish the eggplant, onion and cheese and mix until all gone.
Put 1/2 stick of butter on top in pats.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam broccoli spears until barely tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
Arrange in the bottom of a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Clean and cut chicken in serving pieces.
Marinate in evaporated milk 1/2 hour.
Roll pieces in salt and flour mixture and brown.
Arrange in Dutch oven and pour sugar, soy sauce, water and m.s.g. mixture over the chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes, basting twice.
Garnish with chopped green onions.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain off fat.
Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions.
Mix ground chuck and macaroni. Add tomato soup.
Season to taste.
Stir together and heat.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Cook ribs in boiling water until tender.
In saucepan, combine remaining
ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Grill ribs basting frequently with sauce.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Boil water.
Add sugar and tea.
Cover and brew for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Remove tea bags.
Tie spices in bag and add to tea.
Let set for 30 minutes, then remove bag of spices.
Add jello and juices.
Heat and serve piping hot or good with ice.

title: basic pie recipe for sugar-free pie
directions: Stir together the cornstarch, Karo syrup and water.
Put on stove and cook until clear.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add sugar-free jello and cook 2 minutes on low heat.
Use 6 packets of Equal in 1 quart of fresh or frozen strawberries.
Combine with cornstarch mixture and put in baked pie crust.
Put Cool Whip on top when cool.
Place in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip currant cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray large cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, beat together margarine, pineapple juice concentrate, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg until light and smooth.
In separate bowl, mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to margarine mixture in 3 parts, beating until incorporated after each addition.
Stir in currants and chocolate chips.

title: never-use-a-mix wonderful brownies
directions: In a medium saucepan melt chocolate with the butter.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat like mad!
Stir in 1/4 cup flour (yes, only 1/4 cup!), salt and nuts. Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cook, cut and "Go Crazy"!!

title: creamy chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Grease oblong baking dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inches.
Layer chicken and broccoli in dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli.
Arrange cheese slices on soup mixture.
Mix baking mix and margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with tomato slices, if desired.

title: sugarless apple dessert
directions: Combine gelatin, apple juice, cinnamon and nutmeg in skillet; mix well.
Cook on low heat 1 minute until gelatin is dissolved. Add apples and cook 15 to 20 minutes; stir.
Then add margarine until melts.
Remove from heat.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Serve.

title: stuffed chicken shells
directions: Cook shells using package directions; drain and cool. Prepare stuffing mix using package directions. Combine with chicken, celery, onion and salad dressing; mix well. Spoon stuffing mixture into cooked shells. Chill in the refrigerator overnight. Place in baking pan. Pour mixture of chicken soup and water over shells. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen salad
directions: Stir all together and fill up cake papers in cupcake pan. Place in freezer until frozen, then remove and place in plastic bag until ready to use.
Serve on lettuce leaf with dab of salad dressing on top.

title: mother's waffles
directions: Mix together.
Bake on heated waffle iron.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and gradually add sugar.
Beat eggs in, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
One day aging improves flavor.

title: marinara sauce*
directions: In a large porcelain-lined pot, over high heat:
Add olive oil and heat to medium temperature.
Add chopped garlic and cook garlic until very light, golden brown in color, stirring continuously.
Add fresh basil and fresh parsley, stirring with garlic.
Empty only the juice from cans of tomatoes into pot. Break tomatoes by hand into bite-sized pieces over pot and add to mixture, stirring frequently while adding tomatoes.
(Tomatoes may be put through a food mill instead of broken by hand.)

title: double cheese ham skillet
directions: Spread ham slices with cream cheese.
Top each with green onion; roll up.
Combine butter with 1/3 cup water in large skillet; add rice with seasoning packet and peas.
Bring to a boil, stirring to break apart.
Place ham rolls on rice.
Cover. Heat on medium-low 5 to 10 minutes.
Top ham with cheese spread. Cover.
Heat 2 minutes more until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings, 2 rolls each.

title: mustard potato salad
directions: Mash egg yolks. Add 1 to 2 tablespoons vinegar and 3 to 4 tablespoons yellow mustard.
Mix well.

title: no cook lemon pie
directions: Combine milk, lemon juice and food color; blend well.
In small bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff but not dry.
Gently fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into pie crust. Top with Cool Whip.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, tuna, celery, green pepper, onions and pimiento.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate. Serve on lettuce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: a busy teacher's recipes
directions: Have a wonderful day at school.
On your way home, take your pick of one of the delicacies and enjoy!

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburger until done.
Place all ingredients and hamburger in large pot and cook on low for 1 hour.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling water and salt until done.
Grate cheese and add to grits along with butter.
In a measuring cup, break eggs (lightly beaten) and fill with milk to reach 1 cup level. Combine with grits and mix well. Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great with ham, sausage or bacon.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and shape into loaf.
Place in shallow baking dish. Pour 1 cup of tomato juice over it.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Fifteen minutes before done, brush with ketchup.
Return to oven.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour corn meal into bowl.
Pour 3/4 cup boiling water over meal.
Cover and cool.
Add salt, sugar and egg.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to first mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add melted butter.
Pour into a deep greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, peanuts and gumdrops in a large pan.
Heat last 3 ingredients and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Press into greased angel cake pan.
Put in a layer and press down with fist and repeat until all mixture is in pan.
Slice with serrated meat knife.
Best if left to set for a few hours before cutting.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat soup (undiluted) until warm.
Dissolve gelatin.
Add cream cheese and remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill well.

title: chicken cranberry layer
directions: Dissolve 1 package gelatin in water over low heat.
Add the cranberries, pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch pan until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Cover with 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: pancakes(weight watchers)
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook well.
Equals 1 bread serving or 1 egg.
Serves 1.

title: mock turtle soup
directions: Brown the beef and drain off the grease.
Crush the gingersnaps.
Put beef and snaps in hot water; let set 10 minutes. Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Cook for 3 hours on low heat.
Add lemon last hour and add eggs last 1/2 hour.

title: hamburger minestrone soup
directions: Simmer for 1 hour. Put in soup bowl and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve with garlic bread.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Pour warm water in mixing bowl and add yeast. Stir until dissolved. Add sugar, salt, margarine, egg and 3 cups of flour. Mix well and add remaining 1/4 cup flour to make dough stiff and smooth. Knead dough for 8 minutes on a floured surface. Wrap dough in wax paper and store in refrigerator for 2 to 24 hours. When ready to bake, cut dough into pieces. Roll and shape pretzels. Place on a greased baking sheet. Brush each pretzel with egg yolk and sprinkle with coarse salt. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Pour boiling water over puddings and jello.
Cool until thick. Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: ham casserole
directions: Make white sauce of 3 tablespoons butter, flour and salt.
Add milk.
Moisten crumbs with remaining butter.
Alternate layers of crumbs, eggs, ham and mushrooms in greased casserole dish.
Pour over white sauce.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy anchovy dip
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well; keep refrigerated.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix well; cook for 2 hours, uncovered.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Put in 8 pint or 4 quart jars and seal.
Turn jars upside down for 10 minutes.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix together.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix well.
Pour in casserole dish and refrigerate.

title: jon hagel cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo and sugar.
Mix together in separate bowl the flour, cinnamon, egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix the two mixtures together and place on greased cookie sheet in even layer. Beat egg white stiff and add 1 teaspoon water. Spread over dough. Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Cut in desired shapes when warm.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In medium bowl, combine sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar, and juice.
Gradually beat in oil until mixture is thick and smooth. Stir in poppy seed.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: shrimp spread
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill to blend flavors.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Stiffen with flour.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut with a cookie cutter.
Bake at 350°. Makes a bunch of tea cakes.

title: country style dressing
directions: I add celery seed, also.

title: chicken and ham rolls
directions: Skin and bone chicken breasts.
Combine egg, water and 1 tablespoon of mustard, mixing well. Set aside. Combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon white pepper.
Set aside.

title: french raisin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and bake in uncooked pie shell for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in cocoa.
Get hot, not boiling.
Stir in powdered sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put aluminum foil greased with butter or wax paper into baking pan.
Spread fudge.
Allow to cool.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese with dry seasoning mix and 2 tablespoons milk. Spread on bread. Put thin slice of cucumber on top and sprinkle with dill.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Score fat edges of ham slices.
Place on broiler rack 3 inches from heat.
Broil 3 minutes; turn.
Poach eggs; keep warm.
Place bun halves on broiler.
Broil until light golden, but broil ham 3 minutes.
Place ham on buns.
Top with poached eggs.
Pour easy or mock Hollandaise sauce over all.
Serve with a tossed green salad. Makes 6 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Simmer broccoli and onion in chicken broth, water and bouillon cubes until broccoli is tender.
Add butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix flour with part milk.
Add flour mix and remaining milk to soup.
Heat, but do not boil (will cause broth to curdle).

title: special slaw
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: buttermilk custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour and margarine.
Beat eggs separately and fold into mixture.
Add buttermilk and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese delights
directions: Toss everything but the flour into a bowl and mix.
Blend in flour and mix with your hands.
Form into a long roll.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
You can freeze these and bake later.

title: apple fool
directions: Slice the lemon and place in a pan with the water and 1 1/2 cup sugar.
Bring to a boil; reduce the heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Peel, core and slice the apples; add to the syrup and cook for 10 minutes.
Drain and discard the syrup and lemons. Puree the apples in a blender and refrigerate until well chilled. Beat the cream until thick; add 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla and blend with the apple puree.
Pour into individual bowls and chill before serving.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Cook bacon and/or sausage.
Cut into pieces. Toss bread and cheese by hand and put in casserole dish.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over the bread and cheese. Add pieces of bacon and/or sausage.
Mix. Set in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: holiday cheese spread for crackers
directions: Combine margarine, cream cheese and dry Italian dressing mix. Spread on crackers or rye bread.
Top with a thin slice of cucumber and a dash of dill weed.
Serve.

title: rye bread
directions: Mix the yeast with water and let set. Heat milk to warm stage. Add sugar, salt, oil, wheat germ and caraway seed. Stir. Add molasses, rye flour and 2 cups unbleached flour; work in well. Let stand 30 minutes (covered in warm place); work in remaining flour. Knead at least 50 times. Place in a large oiled bowl in a warm place and let rise until doubled. Knead and punch down and let rise again. Put in oiled pans and let rise again. Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Set on racks and let cool a few minutes. Remove from pans. Let cool completely. Store in freezer bags in freezer.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on counter tops for cooling cookies.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg and beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add to mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Mix ingredients together, and press into bottom of 11X13 sheet cake pan.

title: apple dump cake lite
directions: Add all ingredients in order into a large baking dish.
Do not stir.
Pour melted oleo over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not peek!
You can also spray your dish with Pam so it won't stick.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: In a large bowl place Special K cereal.
Heat jar of peanut butter in a pan of hot water.
Bring syrup and sugar to a slow boil (boil 30 seconds).
Add oleo, stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal, mix well.
Roll in small clusters or spoon out. Place on wax paper until cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: kathleen's light pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs, then combine the other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells (makes 2 or 3, sometimes 4, according to size of pie shells).
Sprinkle tops with cinnamon.
Bake 5 minutes in moderate hot oven, 450°.
Turn to slow 350° or 375° and bake approximately 40 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Put sugar, Karo syrup and water in saucepan on low heat.
Stir until sugar is melted.
Let cook without stirring to 250°.
Just before it gets done, beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup over egg whites while beating until it gets thick.
Add nuts just before dropping on waxed paper.
(A candy thermometer is a must.)

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tuna gumbo
directions: Melt margarine in large pot and add onion, fresh pepper and garlic.
Saute for about 5 minutes.
Combine flour and chicken broth; mix thoroughly.
Add to onion mixture, stirring constantly. Add tomatoes and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: haddock in lemon sauce
directions: Thaw frozen fillets.
Arrange fish in a single layer in heat-proof platter or shallow baking pan.
In small saucepan, combine lemon juice, butter, onion, brown sugar, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring, until blended.
Pour sauce over fish. Preheat broiler.
Broil fish slowly, about 4 inches from the flame, basting 2 or 3 times with sauce until fish is browned and will flake when tested with fork.
Sprinkle with paprika after final basting.
Arrange fish, cooked baby carrots and asparagus spears on platter and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chinese-style vegetables
directions: In medium skillet, mix water and vegetables.
Cover.
Steam 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring several times.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in soy sauce.

title: quick cheesecake
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Add sugar.
Pour into crust.
Top with fruit filling.

title: strawberry-cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups water brought to a boil; add strawberries and blend until berries are thawed.
Add drained pineapple and pecans.
Pour half of mixture into flat dish and chill.
Whip-blend sour cream and cream cheese.
Spoon over the chilled Jell-O mixture.
Spoon remaining Jell-O over the cream layer.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: zesty meatballs
directions: In bowl, thoroughly mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, crumbs, egg, celery and 1/4 teaspoon ginger.
Shape into 50 meatballs.
Arrange in jelly roll pan.
Broil about 10 minutes or until done, turning once.
Drain.
In skillet, stir in remaining soup, water, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, garlic and 1/4 teaspoon ginger.
Heat over low heat.
Add meatballs; turn to coat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: dorothy's chili
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef over medium heat.
Drain off the fat.
Using a fork crumble the cooked beef into pea size pieces.

title: taco roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on tortillas.
Roll tortillas and use toothpick to hold in place.
Place in a covered container and chill up to 2 days.
Slice rolls into 1-inch pieces and serve with picante sauce.
Party favorite!

title: guacamole dip
directions: Squeeze lemon juice on peeled avocados.
Add cream cheese and mix in blender until smooth.
Add onion, salt, pepper, garlic salt and picante sauce to taste.
Serve with sliced bell peppers, cauliflower and cucumbers.

title: four-layer chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour and nuts together.
Melt margarine and pour into flour.
Stir well and press into bottom of large Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until light brown. Cool.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except hash browns in a bowl.	Spray 9 by 13 inch pan with Pam/oil; pour in frozen hash browns, top with sour cream mixture and sprinkle corn flakes topping over top.
For topping, mix corn flakes and 1 stick melted butter.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mushroom-barley casserole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add barley and brown lightly.
Add salt and pepper.
Put into 3-quart casserole.
Add broth and mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: five year pickles
directions: Make brine of 1 gallon of water and 1 cup coarse salt.
Pour over cucumbers; weight down.
Soak for 2 weeks.
Take out of brine and soak overnight in cold water.
Take out of water and slice 1/4-inch.
Mix alum in enough water to cover.
Soak for 24 hours. Don't rinse.
Heat vinegar to boiling point.
Pour over cucumbers and let set for 24 hours.
Have crock or jar ready; place layer of cucumbers, layer of sugar and spices until all sugar and spices are used.
Weight down and cover with cloth.
Can be used next day but the older they are, the better.
Don't add any vinegar; it will make its own.
I left them in the jar for a couple of months, then put in quart jars.
They do not have to be sealed.

title: hot dog dinner soup
directions: Mix, heat and serve.
Great with green salad and corn muffins.

title: easy dip
directions: Mix the shrimp sauce and cream cheese together.
Fold in clams.
Serve with Sociable crackers or your favorite.

title: amy's taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco mix thoroughly.
Spread evenly in long cake pan.
Put a thin layer of lettuce, then a thin layer of tomatoes and top it with a thin layer of Cheddar cheese.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown strips of steak in oil.
Add onions, soy sauce, sugar, seasonings, green peppers, tomatoes and 1/2 cup water.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add cornstarch with a little water and cook until all ingredients are tender.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into melted butter.
DO NOT STIR.
Pour 3 cups of fruit (peaches or any kind) into mixture.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: golden potato salad
directions: Combine milk, mustard, sweetener, vinegar, salt into a small bowl and beat until light and fluffy.
Mix well with potatoes, onion, parsley and celery.
Hard-boiled eggs may be added, if desired.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Melt baking chocolate; set in fridge to cool.
Cream margarine.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in cool, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at time, beating 5 minutes each.
Turn into pie crust and chill 1 hour.
Top with layer of Cool Whip.
Garnish with chocolate shavings from Hershey bar. Keep refrigerated.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add gelatin to the hot Jell-O; stir to dissolve.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple, wine, nut meats and mix by turning with a wooden spoon instead of stirring. Refrigerate in large or individual molds.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and set aside.
Cook bacon or sausage and fry the grease in a separate container to be used later.
Chop up onion and green pepper and saute them with a little of the meat grease.
After the pepper and onion cook, put in the cabbage; add meat grease in teaspoons and cook on medium-high.
Add carrots, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes.
Turn heat to simmer and add meat and seasoning.
Cook until tender.

title: orange cranberry turkey
directions: In a large kettle or covered pan, bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat and add turkey breast.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until turkey is fork-tender. Remove and let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook liquid down or thicken with flour for sauce.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix together in large bowl cream cheese, chopped onions, chopped green pepper, Lawry's seasoning salt and pineapple (very well drained).
Mix together until well blended (May need to use hands).
Add 1 cup pecans pieces and mix until blended again. Shape into ball and put on platter. Top with 1/2 cup pecans and chill for 1 hour.
Eat with Toll House crackers.

title: beth's salad dressing
directions: Combine and shake well.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix blueberries together.
Spread out smooth.
Then sprinkle with pecans, if desired.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top, then pour melted butter over dry cake mix and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Combine soups, water, butter and mushrooms; heat.
When warm, remove 1 cup mixture.
Add rice and pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place chicken on top.
Cover with 1 cup soup mixture.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers into thin slices.
Put on a plate and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with paper towels and another plate and put weights on top (such as 5 pound bag of flour) for about 1 to 2 hours.
Cut rounds of bread.
Spread with mixture of 8 ounces cream cheese and small amount of sour cream and lots of herbs.
I find mint a must.
Chives are also great.
Onion may be substituted for chives.
Place cucumbers on top of the cream cheese-herb mixture.

title: spareribs
directions: Bake spareribs for 1 hour, covered, at 350°. Drain grease and cut into pieces. Baste with Russian dressing; bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Baste once in between. Broil for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Sprinkle over dough.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: french market soup
directions: Sort and wash 2 cups bean mix; place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans and soak overnight.

title: daffy cake (chocolate)
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Mix, by stirring, as little as possible (do not use beater).
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (two 9-inch pans) or for 35 to 40 minutes (9 x 13-inch pan).

title: date bars
directions: Beat egg and add sugar gradually.
Add milk; blend in the flour to which has been added the baking powder.
Mix dates and nuts together with part of the flour.
Add to cake mix with vanilla. Pour into an oiled baking dish and bake about 30 minutes in moderate oven.
When sufficiently baked, remove from pan and place on rack for a few minutes.
Cut the cake into halves.
Then cut each half into narrow strips about 1-inch wide and 4 1/2 inches long.
Roll each strip in powdered sugar and store in a tightly covered box.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Butter baking dish.
Cook broccoli until tender and drain. Put in baking dish.
Dot with 1/4 of butter and slice cheese to cover broccoli.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Add remainder of butter over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles and crumbs brown.

title: goulash
directions: Heat saucepan.
Cook meat.
Stir tomato sauce in it.
On the side, cook Ramen until soggy.
Mix Veg-All and all ingredients together until warm, then serve.

title: mr. williams' peanut brittle
directions: Cook Karo syrup and sugar to hard crack (300°), about 20 minutes.
Take of heat.
Add soda.
Stir in and immediately pour into greased cookie sheet.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry together the hamburger, onion, salt and pepper to taste. Set aside. Simmer together for 5 minutes the undiluted mushroom soup, undiluted tomato soup, thyme, pizza seasoning, oregano, garlic and rice.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: In pot, melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper over medium heat.
Add milk gradually until thickened.
When mixture is thickened, add cheese.
When cheese has melted, pour cooked potatoes in large baking dish, sprayed with Pam, and cover with cheese mixture.
Bake at 400° until bubbly and top has browned a little.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Add eggs and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour and baking powder.
Beat.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Cut okra and set aside. Cook onions, garlic and pepper in oil in large skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly. Add okra, salt, pepper and hot sauce. Simmer for 25 minutes or until okra is tender.

title: black bean-and-rice burritos
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Combine spice blend, cumin and black beans in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Remove from heat; stir in rice. Spoon about 1/3 cup bean mixture down center of each tortilla. Top each with 2 tablespoons cheese, 1 tablespoon green onions, 1 tablespoon salsa and 1 tablespoon yogurt.
Roll up.
Yields 6 servings (serving size:
1 burrito).

title: family recipe for marinated pork chops
directions: Mix and marinate pork chops for 2 to 4 hours.
Stir often. Cook on grill until done.
Very tender.

title: pie crusts
directions: Mix flour, cream cheese and butter with finger tips.
Add sugar, salt and water; mix well.
Let rest 12 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Skin chicken, if desired.
Mix sour cream, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix bread crumbs with about 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Dip chicken in sour cream mixture. Roll in crumbs.
Place in baking dish which has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir in corn and milk.
Pour ingredients in buttered casserole. Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Stir after cooked for 25 minutes. Return to oven and let cook for another 20 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Half hard-boiled eggs lengthwise and remove yolks.
Place yolks in a bowl; mash with a fork.
Add mayo, mustard and vinegar; mix well.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Stuff egg white halves with yolk mixture.
Garnish with paprika or parsley, if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: three-cheese sandwiches
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Grate extra sharp cheese.
Mix all the cheeses together, a little Worcestershire, onions and enough mayonnaise to make the mixture spreading consistency.
Spread between 2 slices of bread.
These make nice party sandwiches when sliced into small diagonals or squares.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix Dream Whip (as stated on box), cream cheese and sugar together.
After you mix thoroughly, beat on high for 5 minutes. For crust you need graham crackers (directions on box).
After you have crust, layer cherries and whip cream mixture until you run out.
Sprinkle a little of cracker crumbs on top.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell and cool completely.
Mix cream cheese with milk; whip and pour into pie shell.
Pick out least and smallest berries and mix with water.
Simmer 5 minutes; add cornstarch and sugar.
Cool until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Pour over cream cheese. Garnish with remaining berries and chill.

title: taco spread
directions: Blend sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning. Spread thinly over serving dish. Layer with shredded toppings.
Keep chilled until serving. Serve with Doritos.

title: schrafft's chicken ala king
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and paprika.
Blend, adding slowly and stirring, hot chicken stock, heavy cream and milk which has been scalded.
Cook 5 minutes over low heat, stirring.
Remove from heat and add chicken, pimentos and mushrooms that have been sauteed in margarine and eggs that have been slightly beaten. Serve on toast.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Heat juice to boil.
Add jello and dissolve.
Add cold water. Add pie filling and pineapple; stir well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish and set.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and sour cream.
Spread on top and put on nuts.
Chill.

title: stewed fish
directions: Place fish in pan. Add 1/2 cup of water, salt, pepper and grated onion. Cover the pan with a top and let stew for 30 minutes.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in water. In saucepan, pour gelatin and add tomato soup; bring to a boil. Take off heat and add in cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, mayo, celery, onion and salmon. Pour into a mold and place in fridge for at least 3 hours.

title: grandma's new england sauerbraten
directions: Brown meat on all sides in hot shortening in Dutch oven. Season with salt and pepper.
Add berries, onion, celery and water. Cover tightly and cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add water, if needed.

title: cheese strips
directions: Fry and crumble bacon.
Grate cheese into medium-sized bowl. Add bacon, onion, almonds, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Trim bread crusts and cut each slice into 4 strips.
Spread mixture on each strip.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Store frozen strips in a plastic bag to use when desired.
When needed, place frozen strips on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: regal rump roast
directions: Rinse 3 to 5 pound Regal rump roast.
Sprinkle meat tenderizer over roast, then prick meat with fork tines.
Cover meat completely with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in same marinade sauce at 225° for about 4 hours.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add other ingredients and stir until sides of bowl are clean.
Press into pizza pan and bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Add favorite topping.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine oats, flour, brown sugar and baking soda.
Stir in melted margarine.
Press mixture into a lightly greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add the molasses and egg.
Beat well and add the remaining ingredients.
Chill; form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar, or just dip in top half.
Place on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix vegetable oil, white sugar, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla. Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar with 1 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over top of cake before baking.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage in medium size pieces.
Spread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat and onion in a large skillet, breaking up meat with a large spoon, as it cooks.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture over cabbage.

title: best ever meringue
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until peaks are stiff.
Add marshmallow cream and beat until stiff.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, oleo and pecans and press into
9 x 13-inch pan; bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: no meat stuffed peppers(heart healthy)
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Parboil for 5 minutes.
Drain and place in baking dish.
Saute onion and garlic powder in margarine. Stir in 1 can tomato sauce, cooked rice, 1 cup cheese and oregano.
Spoon into peppers.
Cover with can of tomato sauce. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake until melted.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Stir together.
Spread evenly in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Save 1/3 of this mixture after cooking to spread on top.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Blend the 5 egg yolks, cream cheese and sour cream.
Melt butter; mix with cooked noodles.
Mix buttered noodles with above mixture.
Beat egg whites with sugar until creamy.
Add to noodles.
Put in greased 8 1/2 x 11-inch casserole pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes. Sprinkle top with 2 tablespoons sugar and ground cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until set.
Serve warm as a dessert or a side dish with a light meal.

title: sausage snacks
directions: Brown sausage and break up into little pieces; drain.
Cube the cheese and add to pan with browned sausage.
Stir over low heat until cheese has melted.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add apples.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook in top of a double boiler until butter is melted.
Store in refrigerator.

title: corn bread
directions: Dump all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Add egg and over 1 cup and 1/4 of buttermilk.
Stir well.
Add small amount of water if too thick.
Put in 2 tablespoons of Crisco or bacon dripping in iron skillet and let get hot.
Pour cornbread mixture in skillet. Bake in oven at 450° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
If not browned on top when 15 minutes are up, put under broiler to brown.

title: peg's chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked chicken in bottom of dish.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Top this with the soups.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Place on top of soup layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Tastes like Thanksgiving dinner.

title: apple bar dessert
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Add cinnamon and sugar.
Mix well and let stand to form juice while mixing crust.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Layer frozen Tater Tots in large casserole dish.
Brown the ground beef and layer on top of Tater Tots.
Spoon on the soup and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for about 25 minutes or until cheese is lightly browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and put in large pan (13 x 9-inch).
Cover with cooked broccoli.
Spread soup over broccoli.
Spoon Cheez Whiz over the soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: desiree's hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Add flour, salt and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Combine soup, water and sour cream in a bowl.
Stir into meat mixture, add parsley.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain, spread on platter.
Cover with meat mixture.

title: no flour fruit cake
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan with brown paper, then wax paper. Set can of milk in hot water.
Mix other ingredients, then add milk.
Mix lightly.
Fill pan and bake at 325° until brown on top, about 1 hour.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix pineapple and bread crumbs together into a baking dish. Mix eggs, sugar and margarine together.
Pour over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it starts to brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef in thin strips.
If beef is partially frozen, it is easier to cut.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef. Toss and set aside.
Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
Add beef and cook over high heat until browned.
If not tender, simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Add vegetables and cook until tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to mixture; stir until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through. Serve over rice.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 3 dry ingredients. Mix melted butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla together until thick and yellow; add dry ingredients gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brownies test done.

title: never fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In a medium saucepan, stir together the sugar, milk and salt.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add butter and boil until a small amount forms a soft ball when dropped into very cold water (not ice water).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Beat and pour into buttered pan.

title: granola bars
directions: Heat corn syrup to boiling.
In a separate bowl, mix granola, raisins, powdered milk, coconut and nuts.
Mix peanut butter in heated corn syrup.
Add granola mix into peanut butter mix.
Add chocolate chips, if desired.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Put filling into baked 9-inch crust.
Top with meringue.
Brown in oven.
Makes a large pie.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Chop shrimp and eggs finely.
Mix in mayonnaise and garlic. Roll into a ball and sprinkle with paprika for color.
Great with Wheat Thins.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light. Mix flour with sugar. Add to eggs and beat well. Stir in syrup, vanilla and salt.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tuna supreme
directions: Cook celery slowly in small amount of water for 10 minutes and drain.
Dice 1/2 of bread into cubes.
Put in bottom of 10 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Mix tuna, onion, mayonnaise, celery and pimento and green pepper.
Spread over bread.
Dice remaining bread, place over tuna mixture.
Mix eggs and milk, pour over top layer.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 12 minutes at 325°.
Spoon soup over top, sprinkle with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: tapioca salad
directions: Dissolve pudding and jello in hot water. Bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. When pan cools, add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: chicken curry in a hurry
directions: Combine the curry powder, cumin, salt, pepper, cloves, water, garlic and tomato paste in a small bowl.
Stir until blended; set aside.
Heat the oil in a Dutch oven over high heat.
Add the onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Add the spice mixture; cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.
Add the chicken, apple, carrots and broth.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, until chicken is cooked and vegetables are tender, about 12 to 14 minutes.
Stir in the peas and heat through.
Serve with cooked rice or couscous. Yield:
4 servings.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine butter and bread cubes.
Mix well and set aside. Combine eggs, sugar and milk.
Beat with electric mixer until just blended.
Add bread cube mixture and pineapple, stirring well. Pour into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: cube steaks with salsa
directions: Start making the salsa.
In a bowl, combine the tomatoes, onion, celery, green pepper, chile peppers, mustard seed, parsley, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir in oil.
Let salsa stand for a few minutes for flavors to blend.
In a skillet, heat butter.
Brown cube steaks in butter on both sides until brown.
Reduce heat. Cook, uncovered, for a few more minutes until cooked to your liking.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange steaks on hot serving plate.
Spoon a little salsa over each steak.
Serve remaining salsa alongside.
Serve with sour cream, grated cheese and tortilla chips.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Line bottom of large baking dish with layer of Doritos.
Spread layer of meat and onion over chips. Pour beans over meat layer, then cover with grated cheese.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab puffs
directions: Drain crabmeat and finely slice. Combine with onion, cheese, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Combine butter, water and salt in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add flour all at once, beating until mixture forms a ball.
Add eggs, one at a time. Blend in crab mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce to 350° and bake another 10 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil 7 cups water and the sugar together for 10 minutes; let cool.
In a second pan, boil 2 cups water.
After it comes to a boil, remove from heat and add the tea bags.
Leave tea bags in water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove tea bags; let cool.
After both mixtures are cool, mix together and add the orange juice and lemonade.
Mix well.
Add brandy.
Put in gallon plastic container and freeze for 24 hours before serving.
Use 2 ice cream scoops with soda mixer of choice (sweet or sour) per serving.

title: winnie the pooh cookies(no baking)
directions: Children can mix the ingredients with a fork (and with clean hands). Shape into balls and store, covered, in refrigerator in a single layer, if there are any left.
Yields 20 cookie balls.

title: hot cheese and broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water, just to thaw.
Drain. Saute onion in butter.
Melt cheese in onion mixture.
Stir in mushrooms, soup and broccoli.
Serve hot in chafing dish with Fritos.

title: spinach-mushroom salad
directions: Place spinach in large bag.
Fasten and refrigerate.
Mix vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic; toss with mushrooms.
Cover and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.
Add oil to spinach in bag. Fasten bag securely and shake until leaves glisten.
Add mushroom mixture.
Shake until mixed.

title: bubble bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths and dip in melted margarine.
Roll in sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon
(having been mixed together). Layer biscuits in greased or sprayed Bundt pan and sprinkle nuts over each layer.
Sprinkle any leftover nuts over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: When softened, mix well.
Make into rolls. Wrap well and refrigerate.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Add flour and baking powder.
Roll into large roll and cool in refrigerator (2 hours). Slice and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: easy broccoli quiche
directions: Precook frozen pastry shell slightly.
In bottom of pan, put raw, chopped onions and broccoli.
Grate white and yellow cheese; put on top of broccoli and onions.
Pour mixture of eggs and milk on top and bake.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place 4 or 5 teaspoonfuls into a mug of hot water.

title: fried bow ties
directions: In medium bowl, with wooden spoon, mix eggs, sugar, milk, salt and 1 cup flour until well blended.
Stir in remaining flour. Wrap dough in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 2 hours or until easy to handle (or place dough in freezer for 40 minutes).

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: pan apple cookies
directions: Boil together the first 10 ingredients for 3 minutes; let cool. Add the flour and soda; mix with boiled mixture.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice, if desired.

title: muffins by the pailful
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Pour water over 100% Bran cereal and set.
Add flour, All-Bran, soda and salt.
Bake in well-greased floured muffin tins for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Do not overbake.

title: candied yams
directions: In 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish, combine butter, syrup and spices.
Add sweet potatoes and roll until coated with liquid. Bake uncovered at 325° for 35 minutes.
If sweet potatoes start to brown, turn them over in the liquid.
If necessary, cover to keep from burning.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions, making 2 (8-inch) layers.
When cool, split both layers, making 4 layers.
Blend together sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Spread all but 1 cup of mixture between the layers.
Blend remaining cup with Cool Whip and spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate.

title: mushroom croustades
directions: Make bread cups; cut circles of bread, missing crusts.
Butter both sides and put into muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Saute 3 tablespoons chopped green onions in 4 tablespoons of butter.
While in foam stage, not brown, add fresh mushrooms.
Cook until moisture is evaporated 10 to 15 minutes. Sprinkle flour over mixture.
Pour whipping cream over this mixture and bring to a boil.
It will thicken heavily.
Add seasonings and lemon juice.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Fill bread cups and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: curried fruit(serves 10)
directions: Drain fruit.
Place in casserole dish.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and curry powder.
Mix well and pour over fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: 22 minute chocolate cake with icing
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients until boiling.
Remove from the heat. Mix together next 3 ingredients.
Add these ingredients to the boiled mixture.
Mix well, then add last 2 ingredients.
Mix together well and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a cookie sheet to make a rectangle. Seal at perforations.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese and place over graham cracker crumbs.
Layer cherry pie filling over the cream cheese. Top with Cool Whip.

title: no bake cookies #2
directions: Put oats, peanut butter and vanilla in bowl and set aside. Mix margarine, milk and sugar in pan; bring to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over oat mixture and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: yurt-style vegetarian stew
directions: Put lentils and split peas together in a saucepan and rinse. Add bay leaf, basil, salt and 2 cups of water, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and let simmer. Add water as needed to keep the peas covered, and adjust heat to keep the mixture at least at a simmer. After about 30 minutes, add the garlic and onion.

title: beef and beer
directions: Roll meat in flour and salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Place in crock-pot.
Place remaining ingredients in skillet to get meat browning and pour over meat.
Cook on low all day.
Serve over noodles.

title: kay jackson's breakfast pizza(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press edges together and up the sides to form crust.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix margarine, cake mix and 1 egg; press into oblong pan. Next, mix 3 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese until creamy. Pour over cake in pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° (may need to bake 5 or 10 minutes longer).

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs and milk. Blend in flour, sifted with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in raisins and oats.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake in hot oven at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pink lemonade punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and mix well.

title: white frosting
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, about 1 tablespoon at a time, until it becomes smooth and glossy. Continue beating and add Karo syrup, a little at a time, beating after each addition, until frosting peaks.
Fold in vanilla.
Makes enough for 2 layers.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Season beaten egg with salt, pepper and oregano; combine crumbs with half the grated Parmesan cheese.
Dip cutlets first in egg, then crumbs; saute in oil until golden brown.
Place in shallow pan.
Cover with tomato sauce and top with Mozzarella slices.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts and browns slightly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: turnovers
directions: Spread out rolls.
Spoon pie filling into rolls and fold. Bake slow at 300° to 325°.
Bake until golden brown.
Remove and cool slightly.
Mix powdered sugar and milk to form a glaze. Spread over turnovers.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Add rice, tomato paste, salt, pepper, mustard and hot water.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy beef and cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add all other ingredients and stir until well blended.
Cover.
Place in oven again (oven should be set at low temperature).
Leave in oven 5 minutes, or more, stirring after 3 minutes.
Serve with Melba toast rounds.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Mix together in order given.
Roll out and cut into biscuits. Dip in melted butter.
Stack two together.
Let raise for 1 hour while covered.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes. Arrange in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Blend soup and water.
Pour over potatoes. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken with powdered ginger, then cut up.
Prepare noodles according to package instructions.
Combine all above ingredients. Put dressing on just before serving.

title: green chili cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9x9-inch baking pan that has been lightly greased (I use PAM).
Bake approximately 20-25 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine egg, potato, sugar, butter and shortening in a mixing bowl; mix well.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Dough will be softer than regular biscuit dough.

title: pumpkin cheesecake dessert
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.
Beat on low until mixture is crumbly. Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk, 2 eggs, rest of pumpkin pie spice, cinnamon and salt.
Mix. Pour onto crust.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Cool, refrigerate until ready to serve.
Cut and top with whipped cream.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: natural laxative
directions: Blend the 3 ingredients.
Take 1 to 2 ounces 1 to 2 times a day.

title: my carrot bars
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add oil, eggs and carrots.
Beat with an electric mixer until combined.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Frost with a cream cheese frosting of choice or merely dust with confectioners sugar.
Store bars, covered, in refrigerator.
Yield: 24 bars.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coffee and return to heat.
Boil for 1 minute. Put vodka in a gallon jug.
Add vanilla bean that has been cut lengthwise.
Add cooled, boiled mixture and place cap on jug.
Let stand 4 weeks.
Stir daily.

title: family cobbler pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar with fruit and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lay margarine in pan and place in oven to melt.
Make batter with 1/2 cup sugar, milk, flour, baking powder, and salt. Pour over butter when melted; do not stir.
Put the sugared fruit on top and bake until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Put sugar, oil and eggs in bowl and beat.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture; blend. Add apples.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: october soup
directions: Cook and stir meat in large saucepan until brown.
Drain fat. Cook and stir onions with meat until onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: quesadillas
directions: Cut cheese into small slices.
Add slices of cheese to one tortilla.
Overlap a second tortilla over the first tortilla to cover cheese completely.
Cook in a pan for 2 minutes; then turn over and cook for an additional 2 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Remove from pan and enjoy it!

title: mazola rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add oil, sugar and salt.
Add sifted flour, one cup at a time (can use electric mixer), until well blended.
Save a little flour for kneading and knead dough for 8 to 10 minutes.
Set to rise until double, 3 to 4 hours.

title: mom brosius' penna. michigan rocks(cookies)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Nuts and dates should be in big chunks to give rocky effect.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Baking degree and time may vary!
Enjoy!

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Combine butter, shredded hash browns, onion and bouillon cubes; add enough water to cover and cook until done. Add soups and Velveeta cheese; cook and stir often.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine thoroughly.
Add whole eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each egg.
Add milk; mix.
Add crushed vanilla wafers.
Mix enough to moisten.
Add pecans and coconut. Mix.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan. Bake 1 hour.

title: broccoli italiano
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain
well.
Arrange in a single layer in an oblong Pyrex.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese. Sprinkle over broccoli.
Season
with
salt
and pepper.
Melt butter with pressed garlic
in
a
small saucepan.
Spoon over crumbs.
Top with paprika.
Put under broiler until crumbs are golden brown.

title: rocky road candy
directions: You will also need a buttered 13 x 9 pan.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Peel and cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Mix sugar and flour together and sprinkle over tomatoes.
Add vinegar.
Mix.
Sprinkle a pinch of allspice in mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Then reduce heat to 325° and bake for an additional 35 minutes.

title: fruit tea
directions: Pour all ingredients together; stir well.
Sweeten to taste. Chill.
Can be kept for several days.
This is a refreshing summertime drink.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix 1/2 package of Italian salad mix with 2 tablespoons butter; melt in skillet.
Saute chicken in butter on both sides.
Transfer to 9 x 13 Pyrex dish.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.	Mix soup, cream cheese and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serve over rice cooked in water using the other 1/2 of Italian dry salad dressing mix.

title: calico beans
directions: Saute onions in a small amount of oil.
Add sugar, mustard, vinegar, salt and garlic.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour over and toss with beans that have been mixed together in a large bowl. Pour into a large casserole and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until hot and bubbly.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix egg and butter and add to dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil and cook until golden brown.

title: good and easy cake
directions: Melt the butter in a 13
x 9-inch pan in oven. Mix in the cake mix and 2 eggs with the melted butter.
In a separate bowl, mix the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour over mixture in pan. Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and egg.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Then add bananas and mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.
I use 2 small loaf pans.

title: moody ranch chicken
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam. Crush Doritos and layer bottom with 1/2. Put layer of chopped chicken. In saucepan, combine creamed soups, onions, Cheez Whiz and tomatoes. Cook over low heat until smooth. Pour over chicken and Doritos. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Put second layer of Doritos and chicken. Spread package of shredded mixed cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: makes-its-own-crust coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given; mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
The middle will appear rather soft.
Properly done, it will have a delicate crust over the top, sides and bottom.
It will be solid enough to cut after it has cooled.
The center will be a perfect cream pie.
If you leave it in the oven too long, you'll have more of a cake.

title: stuffing sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Stir in water, barbecue and tomato paste until well mixed.
Stir in corn and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Stir in stuffing mix just to moisten.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: easy broiled chicken
directions: Preheat broiler; arrange chicken in one layer in pan. Sprinkle with seasonings.
(Can be put in Ziploc and shake.) Broil 10 minutes.
Turn over; broil 10 minutes more or until tender.

title: salmon dip
directions: Drain and debone the salmon.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in fridge until firm.
Roll into ball with chopped pecans and parsley on wax paper.

title: mint sauce(1884 recipe)
directions: Note:
A salt spoon is equivalent to 1/4 teaspoon today.
Mix ten minutes before using.
Serve on lamb chops or sliced lamb from leg.

title: spinach and potatoes
directions: In a large frying pan, fry bacon.
Place bacon on paper towel and pat off excess grease.	Remove remaining grease from frying pan.
Crumble bacon and return to frying pan.
Set aside.

title: spicy thai cucumbers
directions: Heat all the ingredients in a saucepan until dissolved. Cool. Stir into sliced cucumbers. Add a dash of rice wine vinegar. Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: louisiana tea cakes
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Roll out the dough.
Shape into round circles and place on an ungreased cooking sheet after spraying cooking sheet with Pam, if desired.
Cook until cakes get brown around the edges.

title: chocolate town pie
directions: Prepare pie crust; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a small mixer bowl, cream butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 1 hour before serving.

title: gourmet sirloin tips
directions: Saute garlic in hot oil.
Add meat; brown.
Once brown, drain in strainer.
Mix remaining ingredients in Corning Ware dish.
Add meat.
Cut butter in chunks and place on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Melts in your mouth!!!

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook the mixed vegetables; drain. Add celery, onions, cheese and mayonnaise. Put melted margarine in baking dish. Add mixture. Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add seasoning mix per instructions.
Then add can of beans and chilies and heat until warm.
Pam spray casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cooked rice, beef mixture and remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with taco chips or taco shells.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Fix Duncan Hines sugar cookies as directed on box.
Pat out into a pizza pan.
Bake as on box.
After crust cools, put on filling.
Mix cream cheese with orange juice and as much confectioners sugar as desired.
Then, cut up strawberries, kiwi and bananas and place on pizza.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: hamburger pie casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion; drain off excess fat. Mix beef, beans and soup in glass casserole dish.
Beat together egg and potatoes, then spread potatoes on top of beef mixture like a meringue.
Microwave for 10 minutes on High or bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and onion juice.
Add oil gradually, beating constantly.
Add poppy seed last.
Very good on green salads and fruit salads.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer ingredients, starting with sour cream.
Sprinkle chopped scallions on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mouse ears
directions: Flatten biscuits into thin circles.
Fry in hot shortening until light brown.
Drain on paper towels.
While still hot, brush with butter on both sides and sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.

title: custard sauce for fresh fruit
directions: Cook whipping cream over medium heat until it comes to a boil (6 to 8 minutes).
Remove from heat.
In a medium bowl, gradually whisk sugar and cornstarch into egg yolks.
Whisk until mixture is light and creamy (3 to 4 minutes).
Gradually whisk hot cream into beaten egg yolks.
Return mixture to same saucepan; stir in vanilla.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until custard is thick enough to coat back of metal spoon (3 to 4 minutes).
Do not boil because egg yolks will curdle.
Serve warm or cool over fresh fruit.

title: caramel apple sauce
directions: Soften cream cheese; add other ingredients and stir.
This can be heated in the microwave and served warm or cold.
Slice apples or other fruits and dip in sauce.

title: tender-tasting roast
directions: Brown roast in a frying pan until both sides are brown.
Add 1 cup of water until it starts to boil.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and soup mix.
Cook or simmer until tender and done.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 pan.
Sprinkle with rhubarb and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Grate cheeses and mix.
If using whole peppers, they must be washed and drained (remove seeds).
In a separate bowl, beat eggs, milk, flour and salt together.
Use a very large shallow casserole or two smaller ones.
Put half cheese mixture in dish.
Layer peppers, then add remaining cheese.
Pour egg mixture over it. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add salsa sauce on top and bake 15 minutes more.
Enjoy!

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with all kinds of fruit.
Yum, Yum!

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all. Place in loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix beaten eggs and sugar together; add potatoes.
Mix in margarine and other ingredients, one at a time, and mix well.
Put in a casserole dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until marshmallows melt and turn brown.

title: rainbow jello mold
directions: Boil 1 1/2 cups water; mix with 1 box Jell-O.
Pour 1 cup into Bundt pan and cool.
To the 1/2 cup left, add 3 tablespoons sour cream and whip.
Slowly pour over cooled first layer of Jell-O. Repeat for all boxes of Jell-O.
Cool overnight.

title: salsa verde cruda
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor until firmly chopped. Spoon some sauce on top of chilled mussels.
Makes 1 cup.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except marshmallows.
Pour into baking dish. Top with marshmallows long enough to brown.

title: mock turkey
directions: Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Do not let brown.
Bake, covered, and sitting in a dish of water.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and corn meal with fork.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat until thoroughly blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: roast in beer and onion sauce
directions: Brown roast on all sides in oil.
Drain and place in slow cooker.
Combine beer, tomato sauce and onion soup mix.
Blend well.
Pour over roast. Cover and cook 8 hours on low.
Add peppers during final 2 hours.

title: coconut fruit bowl
directions: Cut oranges in half. Scoop out all insides of orange, pour orange jello inside.
Cool, then cut into wedges.

title: peanut-pea salad
directions: Mix together in stainless steel bowl the peas, celery, peanuts, bacon and onion.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash brown potatoes.
Put onto bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Mix melted margarine, sour cream and soup together and pour over potatoes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft-ball stage. Stir soda into syrup mixture. Pour over popped corn and form into balls. Do not stir, but drop the peanuts in, a few at a time, and remove with a teaspoon to waxed paper. An excellent dipping chocolate, all prepared, may be used.

title: 3 hour chicken
directions: Place dried beef in layer or cake pan. Place chicken breasts on top. Cover with soup and 1 can water. Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix sugar and water in a saucepan and boil until it threads off tip of spoon.
Separate the eggs and beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar mixture to whites, then add beaten egg yolks.
Add sifted dry ingredients slowly.
Just fold in, don't overbeat!
Then put into an ungreased angel food pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Invert pan and allow to cool on pan.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Heat oil in hot wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add chicken, green onions and carrots. Stir-fry 3 minutes or until chicken is browned and carrot is tender-crisp.
Add egg; cook, stirring gently, until firm.
Stir in rice and cook until heated through, gently separating grains. Add soy sauce and stir until mixture is well blended.

title: ice cream jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Add ice cream until well blended.
Add drained pineapple and chill.

title: dormouse tea
directions: Combine sugar and water in a pitcher.
